title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand for an hour or overnight in refrigerator.
May substitute low-fat milk and light sour cream for better nutritional value.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Prepare linguine as package directs; drain.
In medium skillet, heat oil and garlic.
Stir in reserved clam liquid and parsley; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add clams, wine and basil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Toss clam sauce with hot cooked linguine.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger sausage salami
directions: Mix and knead as bread and refrigerate, covered, for 24 hours. Knead again and refrigerate another 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and shape into 6 rolls about 10 inches long.
Bake in a 150° oven for 8 to 10 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 5 weeks and will freeze.
(Can put in oven at bedtime and bake all night.)

title: icing for chocolate cake
directions: To make chocolate icing, add 5 heaping tablespoons cocoa.

title: beer bread
directions: Cream margarine and flour.
Add sugar and cream until smooth. Add beer, beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: honeydew salad
directions: Slice melon and avocado into bite size chunks; toss with dressing.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.
Serves 4.

title: baked or grilled potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes (washed and dried) in pan. Coat with olive oil.
Sprinkle with herbs (be generous).
Bake for 40 minutes.
Shake pan occasionally.

title: wrapped chicken livers
directions: Saute chicken livers in butter.
Then wrap in bacon.
Place water chestnuts on top with toothpick.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Then mix broccoli flowerettes, onion, raisins and bacon with mixture and marinate for 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.
Garnish with your choice of the fruit listed.

title: nantucket cranberry pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Place cranberries, nuts and 1/2 cup sugar on bottom of pie plate.
Make batter of 1 cup sugar, butter, flour, eggs and extract; pour over berries.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
If using a glass dish, lower oven temperature.

title: peach pie
directions: In mixing bowl, cream by hand, melted margarine and sugar; add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add milk.
Cover bottom of pie shell with thickly sliced peaches.
Pour mixture over peaches and bake until firm.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix cheese, Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Mix good.
In greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or dish, layer 1/2 cup sauce, 1/3 noodles and 1/3 the cheese mixture.
Repeat 2 times.
Pour 1/2 cup water around edges.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove and let stand 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: homemade biscuits(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Pat in hand.
Place in dish.
Cook until brown at 350°.

title: divinity
directions: In 3-quart bowl cook sugar, syrup and water 12 minutes and 15 seconds on High.
Mixture will spin a fine thread.
Add salt and egg whites; beat until stiff.
Slowly pour hot mixture into egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture loses its gloss and thickens.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: sugarless gingerbread
directions: Sift flour; resift with salt, soda and spices.
Heat to boiling molasses and butter; add sour milk or water.
Beat and add egg.
Stir in sifted ingredients.
Beat batter until well blended, then add vanilla and chopped dates or nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar; stir into fruit mixture. Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil.
Remove from stove and add crunchy peanut butter.
Blend well.
Add cereal, stirring to coat.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13 dish.
Melt chips and 3/4 cup plain peanut butter, stir until smooth.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Refrigerate until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cinnamon raisin walnut pie
directions: Soak raisins in orange juice 30 minutes.
Pour half and half into large mixing bowl.
Add pie filling mix, sugar and cinnamon. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping, walnuts and raisins.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
Remove from freezer; let stand 10 minutes to soften.
Store in freezer.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Grease a pan or dish.
Mix together and pour in dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: hamburger-sausage treat
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add cheese last.
Bake at 350° until warm.

title: brunch
directions: Place cubed bread in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix loose sausage and cheese; spoon on top of bread.
Beat eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk, soup, mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over bread, cheese and sausage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water, 9 to 11 minutes.
Drain.
Cool under cold running water.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine chocolate chips, milk and oleo.
Melt over hot water, stirring until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and peanuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: split pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients (except salt and dill) in a heavy, 4-quart pot.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 70 to 75 minutes, stirring occasionally, until split peas are soft enough to lose their shape and break down to a puree. Remove from heat.
With back of slotted spoon or a potato masher, mash some onions and carrots to thicken the soup.
Stir in salt and dill.
Makes 8 cups.

title: coffee punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ice cream and whipping cream. Pour over ice cream and fold in whipped cream.

title: choke cherry liqueur
directions: Fill 1 gallon jug with vodka, sugar and fresh, washed choke cherries.
Place jug in a cool, dark place and shake jug once a week.
Liqueur is ready by Thanksgiving.
Remove choke cherries from liquid.

title: muffins(serves many)
directions: Pour the boiling water over the all-bran cereal. Add and mix the sugar, oleo, buttermilk, soda, eggs, salt and flour. Stir in the bran flakes. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: green eggs and ham
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham.
Wrap around dill pickle.
Slice about 1-inch thick.

title: agnes' noodles
directions: Mix ingredients with fork and then with fingers.
Roll out and let set for 2 hours.
Cut into strips as wide as you like and cook in beef or chicken broth for about 30 minutes.

title: easier-than-lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in the olive oil.
Add tomatoes, herbs, salt and water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook pasta until tender. Stir all ingredients together except for Brick or Jack cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Boil 4 chicken breasts. Cool and debone. Tear meat in bite-size pieces. Mix flour with about 3 tablespoons water. Make a roux of chicken broth and flour mixture. Heat until thickened. Add chicken pieces, tomatoes, green pepper and onion and simmer until tender. Add to sour cream. Mix and fill tortillas with sauce folding each one over. Top with extra sauce and Monterey Jack cheese and sliced jalapenos. Serve hot.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Put flour in bag; shake a few pieces of eggplant at a time in flour, then dip in egg mixture, then bread crumbs.
Fry in olive oil until golden brown; drain on paper towels.
While frying eggplant, make sauce.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoonful.
Chill.

title: pretty mix
directions: Make a pretty mix!
Use glass bowl!
Layer each vegetable for eye appeal; alternate colors. For example:
Layer shredded lettuce, carrots, celery, grated Cheddar cheese, bacon bits, peas, corn, green pepper, onion, celery and pepper.
Use your imagination.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Saute onion and shredded carrots in butter until tender.
Stir in stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Stir in zucchini.
Add mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Top with an additional 3/4 cup stuffing and 2 tablespoons butter.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mash egg yolks together with mustard.
Add the other ingredients and mix together with wire whisk.
Pour over cooked macaroni.
Mix in carrots and celery.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs and butter in a 9-inch pie pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Melt marshmallows with milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
Chill until thickened.
In a chilled bowl, beat cream until stiff.
Stir marshmallows in mixture to blend; gradually stir in creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fold in food color.
Pour into baked crust. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugars, pudding and vanilla in large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs; gradually add flour. Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: zucchini cobbler
directions: Mix zucchini, lemon juice, sugar and cinnamon together; cook for 20 minutes or until tender.
Mix flour, sugar and oleo together like pie crust.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Put 1/2 of crust in pan making a crust.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour filling on crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Stir and leave until ready to serve; then add 3 quarts ginger ale.
Makes 50 servings.
Sherbet is optional.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add taco mix and a little water to browned hamburger.
Layer bottom of quiche plate with softened cream cheese, layer hamburger mixture on top, next add the salsa and top with shredded taco cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with taco chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli and cut into bite-size pieces.
Pour oil over broccoli, green beans and onion.
Mix and let stand overnight.

title: creamy cornmeal casserole
directions: Mix cornmeal, soda, buttermilk, salt, corn, oil and eggs. Layer into greased 2-quart casserole with chilies and cheese, reserving some cheese for top layer.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: play dough
directions: Add food coloring to water.
Combine all ingredients in heavy pan.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Blend with hands while warm.
Store in airtight container.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken in water (no salt) until very tender.
Remove desired amount of meat for soup.
Add chicken bouillon until salted to taste.
Add carrots, celery, onion and other vegetables. Simmer until vegetables begin to soften.
Then add 1/2 cup rice (if desired) and let cook about 5 minutes.
Finally, add noodles. Finish cooking until noodles are tender.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water with tiny bit of sugar. Scald milk and water.
Add shortening and other ingredients.
When cool, add part of flour also yeast.
Let raise an hour or less which makes a light sponge, then add your salt (1 teaspoon) and the rest of flour.
Work it stiff and let raise for 2 hours or less.
Make into loaves.
This makes 3 medium size loaves.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water, cold water and 7-Up or ginger ale.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add crushed pineapple (drained), marshmallows and bananas.
Stir with fork.
Put in refrigerator. Let thicken like Jell-O.

title: pepperoni pinwheel crescents
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Place 8 slices pepperoni on each rectangle.
Sprinkle each with 2 tablespoons cheese. Starting at the shortest side, tightly roll up each rectangle and pinch to seal.
Slice each roll into 4 equal slices.
Pinch dough together on one side of each slice to seal.
Place sealed side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve with warm sauce, if desired.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: First Layer:
Slice potatoes to desired thickness.
Layer potatoes in bottom of casserole dish, overlapping if necessary.

title: tender swiss steak(or round)
directions: Trim excess fat from meat and remove bone.
Cut meat in pieces for easier handling.
Mix salt, pepper and flour; sprinkle over meat.
Pound seasonings into both sides of meat.
In heavy skillet, quickly brown meat on both sides in hot oil.
Add small amount of water to prevent scorching.
Pour mushroom soup over meat (you may leave some plain, if desired).
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on the thickness of the steak.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: hot dogs in bacon
directions: Cut hot dogs into 4 pieces.
Wrap each hot dog in 1/2 piece of bacon.
Use toothpick to hold together.
Cover with lots of brown sugar. Cover pan with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take foil off and bake an additional 15 to 30 minutes.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, mix in eggs and vanilla. Add milk and flour, alternately blending well.
Add molasses. Pour mixture into greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake is done.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, then cool.
Add milk and blend. Drain juice from pineapple.
Add pineapple and pecans and chill.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and salt. Dissolve soda in 1/4 of persimmon pulp, then add all persimmon to creamed mixture. Add milk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine to make 1 cup.
Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Make a hole and add honey and margarine; mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Melt cheese and butter. Mix all ingredients together in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe the mushrooms with a paper towel to remove dirt.
Remove and mince the stems.
Bring a 2-quart saucepan half full of water with the lemon juice to a boil.
Immerse cleaned mushroom caps; boil for 2 minutes, or just until softened.
Drain on a towel, rounded side up.
Melt the butter in an 8-inch skillet over medium heat.
When foamy, add the minced mushroom stems and celery.
Cook, covered, for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often.
Add the shrimp, lemon juice, thyme, salt, pepper and bread crumbs.
Turn heat to high; cook 30 seconds more, uncovered.
Remove shrimp mixture from heat. Place a heaping teaspoonful on each mushroom cap.
Place stuffed mushrooms on a baking sheet; broil until bubbly, 6 to 8 minutes. Makes 12 to 14 appetizers.
Each contains 22 calories.

title: cowboy stew #2
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce and diced potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook slow until potatoes are tender.
Scoop up on plate and enjoy.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix well
the
first 6 ingredients and roll into balls. Melt the
paraffin
and	chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip and roll balls in chocolate.

title: light oat bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients with moist ingredients.
Divide into muffin tins.
Bake 17 minutes at 425°.

title: bacon cheddar burger
directions: Prepare normal hamburger and top with all ingredients.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine all ingredients in a roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry lemon bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
Place the margarine and sugar in another large bowl; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Add the flour mixture and milk and beat at low speed until the mixture is smooth.
Stir in the lemon rind and blueberries.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Cream together Miracle Whip, sugar and cocoa.
Dissolve soda in the lukewarm water and add alternately to the creamed mixture with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Can be baked in 2 (9-inch) layer pans, if desired.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix 1/2 of cheese with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in crock-pot.
Sprinkle other 1/2 of cheese on top.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: country-style beef and potato casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and browned.
Add potatoes. Cover and cook slowly 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Put into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water; drain and rinse. Combine tuna, mushroom soup, onion and seasonings.
Add a small amount of milk.
Combine with macaroni in casserole.
Place cubed cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about one hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: drachma fried potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into 1/2-inch rounds.
Dry with towel. Heat oil in a large frying pan until hot. Gently place potatoes in oil and fry 10 minutes or until ready.

title: baked potato sticks
directions: Select 4 very large or 6 medium size baking potatoes.
Scrub well and cut each potato into 6 to 8 wedges, lengthwise.
Arrange on a baking sheet.
Combine melted butter and soy sauce.
Brush over potatoes.

title: saute of calf's liver with whiskey tarragon sauce
directions: Bring the stock to a boil in a small saucepan and boil it over high heat until it is reduced to 1 cup.
Combine the flour, salt and pepper in a shallow dish and dip the liver in the seasoned flour, coating it well.
Heat the butter over moderately high heat in a large skillet and in it, saute the liver for about 2 minutes on each side for medium-rare, or until cooked to the desired degree of doneness.
Transfer the meat to a heated platter.
Add the whiskey to the skillet and heat it.

Ignite the whiskey carefully with a match, tipping the skillet away from you and when the flames subside, add the reduced stock, garlic and tarragon. Boil the mixture for 1 minute, or until reduced slightly and stir in the cream.
Spoon the sauce over the liver.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cider mill punch
directions: Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: bean and ham casserole
directions: Place beans in casserole dish.
Place chopped ham on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in bowl in order listed (amounts of first 5 items may vary depending on bowl size).
Spread mayonnaise over top and sprinkle with sugar and then cheese.
Garnish with chopped hard-boiled eggs and crumbled bacon.
Do not toss.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour.
Add butter and mix thoroughly.
Mold 1 teaspoon dough around each olive; shape into ball.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover.
Chill at least one hour. Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut and peel potatoes in 1-inch cubes.
Cook 12 minutes; drain and let cool slightly.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in casserole dish at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: In a skillet combine chicken, water, vinegar, brown sugar, vegetable oil, soy sauce and bouillons.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and liquid has evaporated.

title: chocolate-strawberry pie
directions: Spread ice cream in bottom of crust.
Freeze until firm. Spread fudge over layer of ice cream.
Cover with chocolate Cool Whip.
Freeze four hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving. Drizzle fudge sauce on top and top each slice with a strawberry. Makes 8 servings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325°.
Makes about 9 to 10 dozen.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and add all other ingredients. Pour into an unbaked 9 or 10-inch pie shell and bake until firm at 350° for about 45 minutes or until center of pie is firm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together; can add leftover vegetables, macaroni or fried potatoes.
Pour catsup over top of loaf and bake at 325° until done.

title: nacho mexican dip
directions: Heat ingredients together in crock-pot.
Serve with nachos.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Combine cocoa and baking soda; blend in melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir until well blended.
Stir in sugar and eggs and blend.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chunks.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients well with pastry blender or 2 knives. Chill while you mix filling.

title: iced cappuccino
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed for approximately 30 seconds.
Pour into a chilled glass.
Serves one.

title: mexican rice
directions: Use large skillet, heat oil, add onion, & rice, saute.
Add hot water & tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low.
Cover until all moisture is absorbed.

title: cherry cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix and chill.
Put chilled dough in small tart pans that have been sprayed with Pam.
Roll into balls and press into pans.

title: sue's chocolate almond cheese cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Sprinkle on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Use food processor to mix cheese and next eight ingredients until smooth.
Add eggs and blend.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 75 minutes. Increase oven to 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack. Cover and chill.
Place platter on top and flip.
Remove sides of pan.
Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: latin beans and rice
directions: In heavy skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and green pepper; saute, stirring, until limp.
Add garlic.
Stir in tomato paste.
Add beans, oregano, salt, pepper and water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring now and then, until sauce thickens slightly.
Serve over rice.

title: dump cake
directions: In an oblong cake pan, place cherry pie filling.
Next, put a layer of pineapple.
Sprinkle the cake mix on top and drizzle the margarine over this.
Sprinkle with coconut and then pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beer battered fish
directions: Partially defrost fillets if frozen fish is used.
Cut in pieces 3 x 1 1/2-inch.
Place on paper towels to dry.

title: special potatoes
directions: Place frozen hash browns in 2-quart casserole dish, 13 x 9-inches.
Combine remaining ingredients in microwave and heat until melted.
Pour over hash browns and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rainbow cookies
directions: *One red, one green and one yellow.

title: orange caramel pecans
directions: Melt sugar in juice.
In microwave-proof dish, mix with pecans.
Microwave on full power
6 to 7 minutes.
Stir in microwave until golden brown.
Spread on cookie sheet and separate.
When cooled, nuts will be hard and shiny.

title: corn fritters
directions: Put corn with liquid into large bowl.
Mix all ingredients with corn except milk.
Add just enough milk until mixture is smooth.
Drop tablespoons of mixture onto hot oiled skillet.
Turn when fritters have air holes on top.
Serve with cinnamon and sugar on top or with butter on top.

title: spiced applesauce bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixer bowl; beat until well blended.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and allspice into medium bowl.
Add to applesauce mixture and mix well.
Fold in 1/2 cup pecans.

title: rotini salad(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Cut flowerets from broccoli. Peel stalks. Cut into chunks. Cook broccoli in boiling salted water in medium saucepan over medium-high heat just until broccoli is bright green and tender-crisp.
Drain; rinse under cold water and drain thoroughly. Combine broccoli, rotini, olives, tomatoes, onion and salad dressing in a large bowl. Add cheese.
Season to taste with pepper. Toss gently to coat. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Garnish with carrot strips.

title: mary frances' baked cheese grits
directions: Bring salted water to a boil.
Add grits gradually.
Reduce heat and cook until mixture becomes thick, stirring frequently, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese, butter and Worcestershire sauce while hot and set aside.
Beat egg yolks and add to grits while hot.
If grits are too stiff, add milk as needed to make soft.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into grits.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it spins a long thread.
Pour in raw peanuts and cook until mixture turns a golden color.
Remove from heat and add margarine, soda and vanilla.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Pour into greased pan.
Spread slightly. Cool thoroughly.
Break in pieces.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chopped pecans, until mixed well. Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving with crackers.
Keep refrigerated when not in use.

title: banana snack cake
directions: In a small bowl, mix bananas with lemon juice and vanilla. On wax paper, mix flour and next 4 ingredients.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into 2 pie shells. Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
(Serve with Cool Whip for added taste.)

title: quick fix spaghetti dish
directions: Cook broken spaghetti in salted water for 8 to 10 minutes. Drain.
Cook hamburger, crumbled.
Add Ragu spaghetti sauce.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Add spices (seasonings).
Taste.
Stir well. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, half of cheese and remaining ingredients.
Put into dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: white clam sauce(salsa alle vongole)
directions: Cook until clams are thoroughly heated.
Pour over cooked linguine and enjoy.

title: no bake peanut butter chews
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Stir peanut butter and corn syrup in a medium sized bowl with a wooden spoon until blended and smooth.
Stir in sugar.
Gradually stir in dry milk until blended.
Form rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
To decorate, press tines of a fork into dough in a crisscross pattern.
Store with waxed paper between layers in a tightly covered container.

title: cookie salad
directions: Combine buttermilk, pudding and Cool Whip. Drain fruit and fold into mixture. Crumble cookies and mix into salad. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: quick breakfast puffs
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add milk and shortening.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder twice.
Add liquid and beat for 2 minutes. Pour into 2 hot, well-greased muffin pans.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 400° to 450° oven.

title: peanut butter cluster
directions: Dissolve sugar in syrup; cook until clear.
Add peanut butter and blend.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix and drop on waxed paper using a tablespoon.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: quickie pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Add the unsweetened fruit.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, oil, sugar, orange rind and beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl; add pumpkin mixture.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 or more minutes (or for 1 hour at 300°).

title: beef and mac combo
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, saute the beef, onion and celery until meat is browned.
Add tomatoes and salt;
bring to boil. Stir in macaroni.
Cover
and
cook
over
low
heat, stirring occasionally, for 10
minutes
or
until
macaroni
is tender. Stir in cheese until melted.

title: frosty cucumber mold
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Cool.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream until well blended.
Stir into gelatin; stir until slightly thickened.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in chopped cucumbers, pimento and onions.
Pour into a 1-quart mold. Chill overnight.

title: pineapple deep dish dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place layers of sliced apples and pineapple in baking dish greased with margarine.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples and dot with butter.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix sugar, syrup and salt.
Microwave for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; microwave 2 minutes.
Stir; microwave 2 minutes.
Stir; microwave 2 minutes.
Stir (stop when peanuts are lightly browned).
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Spread onto a well buttered cookie sheet. Cool; break into pieces.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add grated cheese and onions, then the beaten egg and buttermilk.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat where fish are cooking.
When done, they will float. Drain on paper.

title: hot tamales
directions: Mix ingredients well. Wrap shaped tamales in aluminum foil. Boil for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan french toast
directions: Arrange French bread slices in baking dish in a single layer. Pour egg mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for three minutes.
Cut biscuits into small pieces; put into a Bundt pan.
Pour butter, sugar mixture over it.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes or you can use cupcake papers and cut biscuits up into them and pour a little of butter, sugar mixture over it and bake.
Tear off little pieces. Eat like monkeys.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
With a fork, stir in egg, milk and corn until flour mixture is just moistened.
In a large skillet heat 1/4 inch of oil on medium. Drop corn mixture by tablespoon into skillet about 5 at a time. Cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Drain well on paper towel-lined tray.
Dust fritters with confectioners sugar.

title: muhlenberg mud pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate.
Stir together granulated sugar, butter, flour, cocoa, vanilla, salt and eggs in medium bowl.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until edge appears dry and toothpick inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean (center will be moist).
Immediately prick holes in pie with toothpick. Spread 1/4 cup fudge sauce over top.
Cool completely.
Beat heavy cream and powdered sugar in chilled medium bowl with electric mixer on high speed until stiff.
Spread over fudge sauce.
Drizzle with 3 tablespoons fudge sauce.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining pie.
Serves 8.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, combine cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Mix these ingredients by hand until a dough is formed. Form dough into balls (size of your choice) and dip in powdered sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash peppers and remove seeds.
Grind pepper and onions. Cover with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Put in pot and bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add celery and onion.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir in rice, milk, soup (undiluted), water chestnuts, mayonnaise, parsley and salt and pepper (to taste).
Stir until well mixed. Add shrimp and gently fold into mixture.
Spoon mixture into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Crush the bag of cranberries.
Mix with sugar and let it set for 1 hour.
Mix Jell-O in the hot water and let it set up while waiting for cranberries.
Mix chopped celery, nuts and crushed pineapple.
When Jell-O is just about set, add cranberries and apples.

title: chicken and sausage
directions: Flour chicken and saute in oil.
Add pepper and sausage. Saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Add wine; reduce by half.
Add stock; reduce by half.
Add potatoes.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
If needed, add a bit of water.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Use with tortillas, raw vegetables or snack crackers.

title: chicken and peaches
directions: Mix egg and soy sauce together.
Dip chicken cutlets in mixture; let drain and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in 1-inch oil and drain on paper towel.
Bake in covered baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add peaches and juice.
Cover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Cut up cheese loaf in chunks.
Stir in soup and Ro-Tel.
Cook in crock-pot on low.
Great for a large group.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all in a slow cooker. Cover. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine beaten egg with rest of ingredients.
Pour into a small casserole.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for about 40 minutes or until firm.

title: nut filling
directions: Combine nuts, honey and butter and stir over low heat for 3 minutes or until thickened and boiling.
Add beaten egg, lemon juice and rind and salt; cook slowly for 1 minute longer.
When cool, spread over dough that has been brushed with beaten egg.

title: applesauce cake iii
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (175°C). Grease and flour tube pan.

title: cherry salad
directions: Bring to a boil, then cool on stove.
Put in a serving bowl and chill.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat a little.
Add other ingredients and cook on low for 4 hours.

title: pea salad
directions: Cut up lettuce in small pieces and make a layer of lettuce in an 8 x 8-inch square dish.
Drain green peas; put on top of lettuce.
Put chopped green bell pepper on top of this.
Add onion.
Spread salad dressing on top of that.
Add shredded American or Cheddar cheese.
Top with bacon bits.

title: squash pickle
directions: Mix squash, onions and salt. Cover with crushed ice and let stand 3 hours.
Pour off water. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over squash.
Bring to boiling point.
Take off and put in hot jars and seal.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add soups, Ro-Tel, 1/2 cheese and picante sauce; heat until hot.
Place Doritos in the bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour mixture over chips; add the rest of the cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: party burgers
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add meat and onion; brown.
Cook until done.
Add salt, beans, sauce and Tabasco.
Stir to blend and heat through.
Spoon onto toasted buns.
Garnish with onion rings and pickles.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, butter and oil together and cook about 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over popcorn and peanuts.
After popcorn and peanut mixture is coated, add M&M's.
Butter hands well and press into angel food cake pan.
(Press hard as mixture will be stiff.)
Allow to cool and slice with serrated or electric knife.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Put 22 paper muffin cups in cupcake pans.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in each cup.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Fill paper cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Easy.
Can be frozen.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pour the egg mixture over crust.
Bake at 350° 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: newfoundland bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well each time.
Add flour and vanilla.
In another large bowl mix walnuts, raisins, candied cherries and flour.
Toss together and add to first mixture, mix well.
Pour into 4 greased loaf pans so it won't be high.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Insert pick to see if done.
Wrap in foil when cool and refrigerate.
Keeps well.
Also can be frozen.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter, mix flavoring, flour, nuts and 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Shape into balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 10 minutes. Cut down to 250° for 20 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Sift into bowl and make a well in the center.
Beat egg; add shortening and milk.
Pour liquid into well and stir until flour is moistened. Batter will be stiff; do not overbeat mixture.
Fill greased muffin tins about 1/2 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 425° oven until lightly browned.
Test for doneness with toothpick.
Serve hot with butter.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: easy frozen yogurt
directions: In a medium bowl, mix all ingredients. Freeze for 4 hours, stirring hourly for the first 3 hours. Makes 4 servings.

title: play dough
directions: In medium saucepan, blend all ingredients except food coloring until smooth.
Add color as desired.
Mix well.
Cool over low to medium heat until mixture forms a ball and is completely cooked. Will be terribly lumpy at first.
Cool in a loose wrap of wax paper; knead until smooth.

title: salmon ball(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bone and then flake salmon.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Then roll in 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Before serving (or earlier), sprinkle with or roll in chopped parsley.

title: chicken or veal marsala
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add garlic; cook until softened. Flour chicken and cook until brown on both sides.
Remove and put in shallow baking dish.
Add to same skillet (do not wash) the 1 tablespoon butter, mushroom and onions; brown.
Add Marsala wine and bring to boil.
Simmer 2 minutes and pour over meat.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread(low-fat)
directions: Spray 2 bread pans.
Mix ingredients; pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: canned meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Wet hands for easier handling to form balls. Fry, then make a brown pan gravy to pour over meatballs in jar to cold pack 2 hours or 1 hour and 25 minutes in pressure canner at 10 pounds pressure.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Slightly beat water, vinegar and egg and add to mixture.
Chill for 1/2 hour, then ready.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put chicken breasts in baking dish. Mix cranberry sauce, Catalina salad dressing and onion soup mix. Pour over chicken breasts. Cook 30 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes, uncovered, in 350° oven.

title: kentucky chicken
directions: Split chicken as for broiling.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, minced parsley and onion.
Place in medium size shallow dish.
Marinate chicken for 1 hour, turning often.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples. Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender.
Serve warm and, if desired, with cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar.
Add flour and softened cheese.
Cream together.
Place apples in buttered 2-quart casserole and spread creamed mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place in preheated 400° oven and bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl until well blended. Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread into a graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: red sauce
directions: This is used with Beef Enchiladas.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator overnight or until ready to serve.

title: texas barbecue brisket
directions: Rub brisket with salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook/smoke for 7 hours.

title: coal miners pie
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Cook with sauce, peppers, corn, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beef mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: almond custard no. 2(the white house cookbook 1902)
directions: Blanch sweet almonds; pound them as in No. 1 with sugar and mix them well with the egg yolks; then dissolve gelatine in milk. Strain it through a sieve and pour into it the other mixture; stir the whole over the fire until it thickens and is smooth; then pour it into your mold and keep it upon ice, or in a cool place, until wanted.
When ready to serve, dip the mold into warm water; rub it with a cloth and turn out the cream carefully upon your dish.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine oats and cocoa in a bowl.
Set aside.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients and sweeten to taste.

title: green beans italian style
directions: Simmer sauce 15 or 20 minutes.
Add beans to sauce; do not cook beans first.
Cook until beans are done, but still firm.

title: pan fried barbecued chicken
directions: Brown unfloured chicken in frying pan.
An electric frying pan is nice to use with this recipe.
Add barbecue sauce which has previously been mixed in a bowl.
Cook slowly until chicken and celery are well done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients first, then add dry.
Sprinkle sesame seed over mix when in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: glitchy balls
directions: Slowly melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Be careful not to heat too quickly.
Stir occasionally.
When completely melted, remove from double boiler.
Fold in whipped cream and powdered sugar.
Place in refrigerator for approximately 2 hours or when able to form smooth balls.

title: beef and shells
directions: Cook shells until tender.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add ketchup and mustard.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain shells and combine.

title: darleen's cheese cake
directions: Spread rolls in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and enjoy!

title: chinese candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips over hot water.
Pour over noodles and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: dad's goulash
directions: Brown burger with onion, celery & seasonings.
Drain grease and add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix together.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Can serve as soon as cheese melts or bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot pastries
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together. Cut in 1 cup shortening. Scald milk. Cool to lukewarm. Add the yeast and let soften. Add the slightly beaten egg and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well. Divide dough in 4 parts.
On a board dusted with confectioners sugar, roll out in 10-inch square. With pie crust crimper, cut each square into 16 (2 1/2-inch) squares.
Place a heaping teaspoonful of apricot filling in center.
Bring opposite corners together.
Place 2-inches apart on greased sheet.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Remove immediately from sheet. Roll in sugar.

title: rachel's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Place in 9 x 13-inch bake dish. Stir in 2 cans creamed soup.
Cover top with potato tots and pour Cheddar cheese soup on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: quick glazed sweet potatoes
directions: *I peel, cut in wedges and boil about 3 fresh sweet potatoes until done when I use this recipe.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine the above in a large bowl.
Beat 1 minute at low speed, 2 minutes at medium speed and pour batter into pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly in center.

title: cinnamon monkey bread
directions: In Bundt pan, pour butter.
Sprinkle in brown sugar.
Add nuts and raisins.
Cut each roll in 4 pieces using scissors.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon together in bag or bowl with lid. Shake pieces of rolls in this mixture a few pieces at a time.
Drop in greased Bundt pan, adding nuts and raisins on bottom of pan and after each layer.
Melt butter in small saucepan; add brown sugar and bring to a boil until sugar is completely dissolved in butter. Pour over roll pieces.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Take out of pan right away.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups.

title: canada war cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sift flour and baking soda together and add.
Bake at 325° in a loaf pan about 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Mix all in crock-pot.
Heat and serve.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix eggs, salt and enough flour to make the mixture thick. Flour rolling board and pin.
Roll out dough as thin as possible. Roll dough into a log, keeping it floured so it won't stick together. After the dough has been rolled into a log, cut across the log as thin as possible.
Untangle noodles and allow to set about 3 to 5 minutes so they don't get tough.
Drop noodles into a pan of tomato juice or beef broth. Allow to simmer in juice or broth until tender and season to suit yourself.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, water, Karo and peanuts in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil (when the boil begins to boil in middle of pan, begin timing), stirring constantly for exactly 5 minutes. Remove from heat, add margarine, vanilla, salt and coloring.
Cool slightly (under fan about 5 minutes).
Beat by hand until creamy and unglossy.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased foil (which has been laid over newspaper for heat protection).
Cook on medium-high.

title: kwik buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut 1/2 cup margarine into flour with a pastry blender or 2 forks until mixture is crumbly.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter and place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix as listed.
Mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan that has been oiled and floured.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sarah's cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press out of cookie press using star plate.
Shape into rings.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
These can be frozen and used later.

title: pepper sirloin steak
directions: Lightly score edges of steak at 1 inch intervals.
Preheat grill or broiler.
Combine butter, parsley, onion, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and mustard in a small saucepan.
Heat stirring continually, over low heat until butter melts.
Reserve 1/4 of the mixture.
Place steak on grill or broiler pan.
Brush steak with butter mixture.
Cook, basting frequently with butter mixture, about 6 minutes per side for medium.
Place steak on a serving platter.
Cut thin slices across the grain.
Drizzle butter mixture over steak.

title: rhubarb meringue torte
directions: Combine margarine, 2 cups flour, 2 egg yolks and salt in a bowl; mix well.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Combine rhubarb, 2 1/2 cups sugar, 4 egg yolks and 1/4 cup flour.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Beat egg whites in bowl until stiff peaks form.
Add 1 cup sugar, beating until stiff and glossy. Spread over rhubarb.
Bake until brown.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, broken crackers and coconut. Mix and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: chicken egg rolls(serving size:  10; the creative cook)
directions: To make filling in skillet, cook cabbage, celery and onions in oil until just tender.
Add chicken, bean sprouts, radishes, water chestnuts and soy sauce.

title: caramel cups
directions: Mix dough ingredients together, press into tassie pan cups. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: graham cracker fluff
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar and milk.
Cook in top of double boiler until slightly thickened.
Soak gelatin in cold water. Pour hot mixture over softened gelatin and stir until smooth. Chill until slightly thickened.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites, vanilla and whipped cream to the chilled mixture.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, Wesson oil and pumpkin.
Sift 2 cups flour; add salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in loaf pan.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
While still hot, cut, sprinkle grated Mozzarella cheese on each piece and serve.

title: green tomato relish
directions: In a large stock pot, mix ingredients and bring to a boil. After mixture comes to a boil, remove from heat. Pour into hot jars immediately (to prevent tomatoes from softening) and seal. Makes 8 pints.

title: burger goulash
directions: Brown beef in skillet in a little oil.
Add chopped onion; cook until onion is limp, stirring constantly.
Add tomato sauce, then add water.
Stir in seasoning.
Add peas and carrots while still frozen.
Thicken with flour and water mixed to a liquid paste.
Continue cooking until slightly thickened, about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: patsy's christmas morning casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Mix with rice, cereal and 1/2 cheese.
Place in 3-quart casserole.
Mix eggs, soup and milk; pour over sausage layer.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Can be fixed the night before and refrigerated. Leftovers can be reheated and are as good or better next day.

title: fried crab cakes
directions: Mix the crabmeat, salt, pepper, cayenne pepper, flour and Tabasco sauce.
Set aside.
Beat 2 eggs with a fork; then add mayonnaise.
Mix lightly; add to crabmeat mixture.
Gently mold mixture into little cakes.
Beat other egg and dip the cakes into it and coat with bread crumbs.
Deep fry
until toasty brown. Drain on paper
towels.
Serve warm.

title: mom's custard pie
directions: Scald milk; add beaten eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla and pour into unbaked pie shells, pricked with fork.
Sprinkle nutmeg over tops of pies.
Cook at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Check with knife in 30 minutes.

title: good good pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set and brown.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Line 12 muffin cups with baking paper cups. Fill almost full.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, sugar, soda and salt.
Add oil, carrots, pineapple, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Bake in greased, lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: butterfinger milkshake
directions: You can use a blender or mixer.
Mix all ingredients and blend or mix.
Use less milk for thicker milkshake and more for a thinner one.
You also can replace Butterfinger with crushed Oreo cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease bottom of large pan only.
Beat slow for 30 seconds and medium for 1 minute.
Bake about 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: easy vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Mix Ricotta cheese with eggs (beaten) and spinach.
Layer spaghetti sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan; alternate with noodles and Ricotta spinach mixture.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or heated through.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat slowly in oil.
Add vegetables and cook on low-medium until heated.
Combine broth, garlic, ginger, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, cornstarch and pineapple juice.
Stir broth mixture into meat and vegetables.
Cook until sauce thickens. Remove from heat.
Add pineapple; stir to warm.
Serve with egg drop soup and fried rice.

title: strawberry chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan so the cake will be thin; cool. Slice and sweeten the berries.
Chill the berries at least 2 hours.
To serve, spoon berries and juice over a square of cake. Enjoy.

title: cooked fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and mix with other ingredients. Cook in microwave until thick.
Cook and pour over fruit and cheese.

title: mom's best brownies
directions: Blend margarine and Crisco.
Blend sugar and vanilla into margarine mixture, then add eggs.
Mix well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend into egg mixture. Stir in nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Beat together the milk and pudding mix until thick.
Blend in softened cream cheese.
Spread mixture into crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
When ready to serve, drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour above mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle top with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.

title: bliss house cookies
directions: Blend sugar, molasses, shortening and egg together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into teaspoon size balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: tennessee biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll on a floured board until about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter, then place on a cookie sheet and bake at 425°.

title: pink lady cake
directions: Thaw strawberries; mix well and measure 5 ounces for cake, saving remainder for icing.
To make up to 1/2 cup water and juice, take 1 tablespoon of juice from strawberries saved for icing and place in measuring cup.
Add water to make 1/2 cup. Pour cake mix and flour into bowl.
Add jello and mix well.
Add water and juice, salad oil and eggs.
Mix well on low speed. Add 5 ounces of strawberries and blend evenly.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons butter; stir in flour and water until thickened.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and broccoli; add eggs.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking pan.
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat in large greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Mix until smooth.
Chill 3 hours (overnight).
Serve with cut up vegetables.

title: zucchini bread(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 2 (5 x 8-inch) loaf pans with Pam.
Combine egg, egg whites, oil, milk and sugar in large bowl. Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts.
Add all of this to zucchini mixture; stir to blend.

title: snowflake macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake 20 minutes or until edges of cookies are golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Cool on wire racks.
Drizzle with melted Baker's semisweet chocolate, if desired.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Use broth to cook rice.
Toast almonds.
Mix remaining ingredients, along with chicken and rice.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with almonds.
If dry appearance, add chicken broth.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel brownies
directions: In double boiler or microwave, melt caramels and 1/2 cup milk. Set aside.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, 1/2 cup milk and margarine.
Press 1/2 of dough in bottom of pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 350° and remove from oven.
Spread chips over dough and drizzle caramel mixture over chips.
Cover with remaining dough. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or more.

title: cheater's coffee cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, using 2 tablespoons less water.
Pour half the batter into greased and floured tube pan, 10 x 4-inch.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over batter in pan.
Cover with remaining batter. Sprinkle remaining filling on top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Beat in milk, vanilla and egg until well mixed.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt until well mixed. Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill several hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Cook crawfish.
Stir in onion; cook until onion is clear.
Add soups together and cook.
Combine meat and soups.
Simmer on low, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a baked pie shell or graham cracker pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: meatless chili
directions: Lightly saute garlic and onion in oil and water until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes, beans and chili powder.
Cook covered for 1 hour or longer on low heat.
Makes 6 servings, (about 10 cups).

title: gluh wein
directions: Combine all ingredients except wine in 1 cup.
Fill up cup with well-heated, but not boiled wine.
Makes one serving.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, lemon juice and sugar and let set until thick enough to whip.
Prepare 1 package of Dream Whip.
Drain pineapple.
Crush vanilla wafers.
Pat crumbs into well-buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add crushed pineapple to prepared Dream Whip. Whip Jell-O mixture and combine with pineapple-Dream Whip mixture and pour over crumbs.
Save a few crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Let set until thoroughly chilled.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add strawberries, stirring until completely thawed.
Add drained pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Then add pineapple juice to the softened cream cheese and mix until soft and creamy.
Add chopped nuts and spread over Jell-O mixture.

title: german sauerkraut dip
directions: Combine and blend all ingredients at medium speed until mixed. Serve with pretzels.
Store in refrigerator.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in next five ingredients, then nuts. Pour
into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes. Set
oven
temperature
control
at
continue baking
30 to 35 minutes.
Filling should be slightly less set in center than around edge.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix the sugar and shortening, then add mashed bananas, then egg yolks and buttermilk, dry ingredients, flour and nuts.
Last add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is a two layer cake.

title: creamy nut dipped candies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 4 cups powdered sugar, coconut, butter, salt, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until light and fluffy (4 to 5 minutes).
By hand, knead in 1 cup powdered sugar.
(Dough may be soft.)
Form teaspoon around each nut; roll into ball.
Refrigerate until firm (2 hours).

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine milk, shortening and potatoes.
Cook and stir over low heat until shortening is melted.
Remove from heat and place in large bowl with sugar, salt, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Add eggs; mix well.
Cover loosely and allow to stand for 2 hours (the dough will be like sponge).
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.

title: rice and green chili casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
End with sour cream.
Dot with butter and top with cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine onions and butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on saute for 3 minutes, or until soft.
Add 1/4 cup water and stir in remaining ingredients except hot dogs.
Cook, covered, on High for 2 1/2 minutes or until it bubbles.
Stir in hot dogs. Cook, covered, on High for 4 minutes or until hot dogs are hot. Let stand 2 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Line a jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch) with foil.
Place graham cracker squares close together to cover bottom of pan.
Boil together the butter, brown sugar and pecans for a couple of minutes.
Pour over crackers and spread smooth.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and immediately sprinkle the chocolate chips over top.
Spread with spatula as they melt.
May have to melt chips in oven for a few minutes. Let set until cool, then put in refrigerator.
When cold, break into pieces after lifting foil with cookie mixture out of pan.

title: viennese brownies
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and 1 egg.
Set aside.
Melt chocolate and butter.
Beat 2 eggs until fluffy.
Add 1 cup sugar and chocolate mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients; stir to blend.
Pour half chocolate mixture into pan. Spread with cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Can freeze.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork.

title: brown bean cakes
directions: Mash up 2 cups of cooked brown beans.
Add the diced green pepper, onion, corn meal, flour, eggs, black pepper, pinch of salt and condensed milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pat out into cakes.
Place cakes into greased pan.
Fry cakes approximately 5 minutes on each side, or until done.

title: potato cheese patties
directions: Leftover mashed potatoes or instant mashed potatoes may be used.

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients. Dissolve the yeast in slightly warmed buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients, oil, yeast and buttermilk, stirring lightly and quickly until mixed. Turn onto a lightly floured board and knead gently about 20 to 30 times.
Roll out or pat to a 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a floured 1-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Cover and let rise in a warm place for about 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oven tender chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place 1 cut-up fryer chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with syrup, blending well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in sheet pan 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Let cool and top with icing.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in small amount boiling salted water until just tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and combine with onions and green pepper in large bowl.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables in bowl.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl, if desired.
Return leftover carrots to marinade and keep refrigerated.

title: ann's salmon bisque
directions: In pot, melt butter and saute onion and celery until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour and paprika and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in water, salt, dill weed and bouillon over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and is smooth.
Remove from heat and fold in salmon.
Return mixture to heat; stir in half and half and add sherry.
Heat bisque until hot.
Before serving, garnish with celery leaves.

title: crock-pot cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Shape into loaf and place in greased crock-pot.
Cover and bake on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini well.
Sift other ingredients together.
Fold all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and water alternately with flour mixture.
Mix and treat as a cake.
Bake at 350° about 35 or 40 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water until dissolved thoroughly.
Add pineapple.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour half of mixture in bottom of bowl.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Work together and knead.
Roll out and cut into approximately 24 squares.
Press into small tart tins.

title: ranch style potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and boil the potatoes in a large saucepan until tender (just tender, not falling apart).

title: marinated fruit combo
directions: Advance preparation:
Combine melon, pineapple and strawberries.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over fruits. Stir gently.
Chill 1 to 2 hours; stir occasionally.
Makes 6 cups.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Mix and let set for 5 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: chocolate mint dessert
directions: Chop up and mix Oreo cookies with 1/3 cup butter (save some crumbs for the top).

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir together eggs, syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Melt butter and add all ingredients except shrimp.
Bring to a simmer and then add shrimp.
Cook until shells start coming away and the shrimp are good and pink.

title: brunswick chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken backs in large pot with salt until tender. Remove chicken, save broth.
Remove skin from backs, debone chicken.
Into pot add lima beans, corn, tomato sauce, black pepper, sugar, additional teaspoon salt and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Add potatoes to pot and simmer another 30 minutes.
Serves six.

title: rhubarb supreme dessert
directions: Cut rhubarb fine.
Mix flour, butter and 2 cups sugar.
Press in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix the rest of ingredients together well.
Pour over baked crust and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Beat egg whites, 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla until it holds a peak.
Put over top.
Seal to edge.
Bake until meringue is golden brown.
Cool and serve.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide popcorn between 2 ungreased 13 x 9-inch pans.
In saucepan, heat sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt, stirring occasionally until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking over medium heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda until foamy.
Pour on popped corn, stirring until corn is well coated. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Yields 15 cups.

title: cornish hens with orange glaze
directions: Brown hens in butter in skillet.
Place hens in baking dish/roasting pan.
Melt apple jelly over medium heat.
Add cornstarch to hen drippings.
Stir in apple jelly, juice, wine and salt.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Pour over hens.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Elegant!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in one bowl.
Beat together 3 eggs and 1 cup oil.
Pour into flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Grease and flour a 3 x 5 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or bake 4 small loaves for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian bruschetta
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Taste and correct seasoning if needed.
Let stand at room temperature about 30 minutes (longer if desired to attain best taste).
Serve on grilled (or toasted) sliced Italian or French bread (slice bread about 3/4-inch thick).

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Fill cup 2/3 full of milk, fill cup to top with shortening. Sift the 2 cups of flour with baking powder and salt.
Add milk, shortening and egg beaten lightly.
Toss on floured board and knead 20 times.
Roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake 15 minutes in hot oven, 400° to 450°.
Makes 20 biscuits.

title: favorite cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding egg last.
Bake in 425° oven in a well-greased pan for about 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour 6 times before measuring.
Cream sugar and Crisco until creamy and add eggs and flour alternately.
Beat about 4 minutes.
Then pour in a floured and greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
(Don't open door to oven for the first hour.)

title: winter tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags; let set until dark color. Mix with sugar and lemonade.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: crabmeat bake
directions: Melt butter. Add flour, salt, pepper, parsley and chives. Simmer 1 minute, then slowly add milk and cook until thick. Remove from heat. Cool. Add juice and rind slowly, blending well. Fold in mushrooms and seafood. Put in the refrigerator and season with seasoned salt after cooled. Put in baking shells. Sprinkle with cheese and make a ring on the outer edge of the shell with bread crumbs. Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini raisin nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add raisins, nuts and coconut to dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice to package instructions.
Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Combine ingredients in a casserole; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter fingers
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add flour, water and vanilla.
Add nuts last.
(May mix with hands.)
Pinch off small pieces and roll in palm of hand to about the size of your finger.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, roll in xxxx sugar.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly; put into a greased baking dish.
Put in an oven set at 350° for one hour.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix well as any meat loaf.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: turkey sloppy joes
directions: Lightly spray an unheated large skillet with no-stick spray. Add the turkey; cook until no longer pink, stirring occasionally. Drain.
Add the green peppers, onions, tomatoes, carrots and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the tomato sauce, tomato paste, oats and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve the mixture in the buns.

title: "liquid gold" barbecue sauce(grandma masella's)
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add ketchup, water, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt and flour.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough onto buttered pizza pan; sprinkle with white sugar and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool completely.
Mix and spread over cooled cookie dough the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Mix strawberries and glaze; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip; sprinkle with chopped nuts or crushed sugar cookies.
Chill before serving.

title: rice & sausage
directions: Fry sausage.
Drain.
Combine all the other ingredients and add sausage.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.
Stir occasionally.
Use no salt.
Pepper a little.

title: toll house chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter and cool to room temperature. Preheat oven to 325°. In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended. Blend in melted butter. Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts. Pour into pie shell. Bake for 1 hour. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream. May be doubled and make 2 pies.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In 4-quart micro-proof bowl, mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook on High (max power) for 20 to 22
minutes or until a few drops of mixture in cool water forms a soft ball, 234° on candy thermometer.
Do not leave thermometer in oven while cooking. Stir well every 5 minutes during cooking.
Stir in chocolate bits and marshmallow cream.
Stir until well blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix and pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart microwave-safe bowl on High 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave on High 5 minutes or until mixture begins to boil, stirring after 3 minutes.
Mix well; scrape bowl.
Continue microwaving on High 5 1/2 minutes; stir after 3 minutes.

title: ultimate chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour bottoms of 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Mix first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed beat next 3 ingredients 3 minutes or until light and fluffy. At low speed beat in mayonnaise.
Add flour mixture in 4 additions alternately with water, beginning and ending with flour. Pour into pans.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove, cool on rack.
Frost.
Keeps well in refrigerator several days.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown meat and onions in pan.
Add tomato sauce, water and chili.
Blend and add beans, cook for about 45 minutes.

title: corn pones
directions: Bring water to boil. Add bacon grease, salt and onion powder (boil to soften the onion flakes if you add them).
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn meal and baking soda.
Wet your hands and shape in oval corn pones.
Fry about 5 to 6 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix butter, margarine, egg yolk, and vanilla.
Add sugar and flour.
Spread thin on large cookie sheet or two small ones (with sides).
Beat egg white and spread over top.
Then sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes or until light golden brown. Cut into squares as soon as removed from oven.
These get hard in a hurry.
These can easily be stored in a plastic container for a long period of time.

title: chris' date nut bread
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add the nuts, dates, baking soda and salt.
Let stand 15 minutes in a separate bowl.
Beat the eggs; add the vanilla, sugar and flour.
Combine the date mixture with the egg mixture.
Grease a loaf pan and pour in mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: apple raspberry crisp
directions: Mix together the apples, raspberries and 1/2 cup sugar together and set aside.

title: chocolate waffle iron cookies
directions: Melt and cool first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Oil or spray waffle iron.
Spoon dough onto waffle iron in walnut size drops.
Close waffle iron and bake a few minutes until firm. Frost or roll in powdered sugar.
A neat idea for a quick snack or if an oven isn't available.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate zucchini.
Beat eggs until fluffy; mix in oil, sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add the beaten eggs.
Add zucchini and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Bake in a loaf pan.
I use Pam on pan.

title: texas lizzies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and blend well. Add all other ingredients and blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (varies according to individual ovens). Take half of cake batter and pour into greased 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch rectangular pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until done.

title: joyce's homemade fudge
directions: Optional:
Peanut butter chips instead of milk chocolate chips for peanut butter fudge.

title: sesame sticks
directions: Decrust bread and slice into finger slices, enough to fill a jelly roll pan.
Drizzle melted butter or oleo over the bread strips.
Be sure all pieces have some butter on them.
Sprinkle cheese and sesame seed over bread pieces.
Bake in 200° oven 1 hour.
Cool on paper towel.
Store in airtight container.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aaron's dish delish
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and set aside.
Saute bell peppers with ground chicken, making sure the ground chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Add the powdered dressing mix, onion soup mix and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Add cooked pasta.

title: lemon mushroom chicken
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Coat chicken breasts with flour mix.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Brown chicken to light golden brown.
Add lemon juice and mushrooms.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until done.

title: mediterranean soup
directions: Shape meat into 12 small meatballs.
Add oregano to meat mixture before shaping.
Brown slowly in saucepan (use a little shortening, if necessary).
Pour off any excess drippings.
Mix soup and water together; stir into saucepan.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix like pie crust the flour, butter and 1 cup chopped nuts; pat in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: simple apple pie
directions: Place apples in butter in pie dish.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over apples.
Spoon flour mixture over apples. Bake at 350° until crispy brown.

title: cornstarch clay
directions: Put salt and 2/3 cup water in pan and bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with 2/3 cup water and mix well.
Blend 2 mixtures together and knead into clay.
Makes about 3 cups.
This clay can be air dried and then painted.
Store unused clay in airtight container in the fridge.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Blend all
ingredients until well moistened.
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan, well-greased.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: whole wheat carrot-banana bread
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat margarine for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flours, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients and banana alternately to butter mixture, beating after each addition.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.
Yields 15 servings each.
