title: sierra nuggets
directions: Cream together until smooth butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat and add eggs.
Stir in corn flakes and oats.
Sift together, then add to the preceding the flour, soda, salt, mace, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir in coconut, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut pretzel candy
directions: Melt the following ingredients in double boiler:
peanut butter, peanut butter chips and vanilla candy coating.
Mix with broken pretzels and unsalted peanuts.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Spread candy mixture onto cookie sheet. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: baked spareribs "aloha"
directions: Cut after every third rib, about halfway through the strip. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow roasting pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/4 hours.
Carefully drain off all excess fat.
While ribs are roasting, mix remaining ingredients and let stand to blend flavor.
Pour over ribs after 1 1/4 hours baking.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes longer, basting frequently to coat ribs with flavorful sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for one hour.
Cook a day ahead and let mellow overnight.
This is good to give at Christmas.

title: meat ball supreme
directions: Soften bread in milk; drain.
Add eggs.
Mix meats, seasonings, onion and parsley.
Combine all ingredients and form balls.
Roll in flour and brown in hot oil.
Add tomatoes and Kitchen Bouquet.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add water, carrots and celery.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add peas and heat.

title: pizza bread(easy)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 inch pie plate or cake pan. Mix Bisquick, 1/2 cup of cheese, 1/2 cup pepperoni, egg, milk and seasoning.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle rest of cheese and pepperoni. Bake about 20 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Serve warm as an appetizer or with pasta.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: In a pan, mix ingredients well. Cook on high heat until rolling boil. Turn to medium heat and boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Take off stove. Add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream. Add peanut butter until thickened. Put in buttered pan. Add nuts, if desired.

title: upside down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 13 X 9 X 2 inch pan. Line with wax paper and then grease wax paper. Sprinkle coconut in bottom of prepared pan, then sprinkle pecans. Set aside. Combine cake mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl, mix according to package directions. Pour mix over coconut and pecans. Combine cream cheese and butter in a saucepan, cook over low heat, stirring often, until butter melts and mixture is smooth. Stir in powdered sugar. Spoon mixture evenly over butter. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Invert cake onto a serving plate. Remove wax paper and discard.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together sugar, shortening and peanut butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt and add to butter mixture. Beat well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional white sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press candy kiss in center of each cookie.
Return to oven.
Bake another 3 minutes.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Add eggs, milk and flavoring.
Mix well. Stir in melted butter.
Bake in a 300° oven about 1 hour.

title: dry apple stack cake
directions: Cook the apples until done.
Mix all together shortening, eggs, sugar, molasses, milk, flour, vanilla and allspice until thick.
Pour into an 8-inch greased and floured iron skillet. Fill 1/2 full and bake at 350° until done (the toothpick should come out clean).
Stack on top of each other with apples spread between each layer.

title: cheese cake
directions: Lightly butter an 8-inch spring-form pan, coat with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix all ingredients together, except lemon juice, no more than five minutes of mixing.
Add lemon juice and rind slowly.
Pour mixture into prepared pan; bake in a pan of water at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off, let rest in oven 1/2 hour. Refrigerate when cool.

title: marinated carrots or copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots; cook in little salted water in pan with tight cover until fork-tender.
Cool in cold water.
Arrange in glass container in layers with pepper and onion.
Make dressing with remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: key lime cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Make the crust by combining the graham cracker crumbs with the butter and 1 tablespoon sugar in a medium bowl.
Stir well enough to coat all of the crumbs with the butter.
Keep it crumbly.
Press the crumbs onto the bottom and about one half of the way up the sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
You don't want the crust to form all the way up the back of each slice of cheesecake.
Bake the crust for 5 minutes, then set it aside until you are ready to fill it.

title: patio potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel potatoes; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine potatoes, eggs and salad dressing; toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: chocolate delite
directions: First Layer:
Melt butter and mix flour.
Add 1/2 cup pecans and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown in 300° oven (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Cool.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend well in blender.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into a loaf pan.

title: sour cream - cranberry salad
directions: Mix jellied cranberries and 1 cup hot water with mixer or in blender until liquid and smooth.
Dissolve both packages Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry mixture and pecans to gelatin. Pour half the mixture in an 8-inch square pan and chill in freezer until firm (30 to 35 minutes).
Spread sour cream over top of chilled mixture.
Add second half of gelatin mixture over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: angel cherry delite dessert cake
directions: Spray 2 long cake pans the same size.
Mix angel food cake as directed.
Put 1/2 of the batter in each pan.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 325° (watch closely so as not to burn).
Prepare Dream Whip as directed and add softened cream cheese.
Place 1/2 of this over one cake, then arrange pie filling over this.
Place the other cake on top of first one and do the same as before.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, cornstarch and red food coloring and cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon jello mix.
Pour over cooked pie shell lined with fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream until well blended. Serve with fruit.

title: saucy spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients in large shallow baking dish and then add ribs.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 3 hours (turn meat occasionally).

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook fresh potatoes covered in boiling water until tender. Peel and mash.
Measure 1 1/2 cups.
Combine potatoes, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Beat eggs slightly with fork.
Stir eggs, milk and butter into potato mixture.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Place salt, pepper and flour in a paper bag. Shake well. Place 2 or 3 pieces of chicken in bag at one time and shake until each piece is evenly coated.
Drop into hot fat and cook 15 to 20 minutes on each side. Avoid piercing meat to escape juices popping hot fat.
Remove well cooked and golden brown chicken from fire. Serve when cool.

title: quiche aux poireaux
directions: Saute leeks in butter until tender.
Add salmon and dill; toss lightly.
Turn in bottom of pastry shell.
Combine half and half, eggs, flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg to taste and mix until smooth. Pour into shell over salmon mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Place sugar, shortening and salt in large bowl.
Pour boiling water over sugar mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm and stir in eggs.
Sprinkle yeast over lukewarm water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir well, add to sugar mixture.
Add flour and mix well with a wooden spoon.
Cover with foil and place in refrigerator for 2 hours or longer.
Roll out on floured surface into rectangle, brush with melted butter.*
Roll up as for jelly roll, cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased muffin cups.
Let rise 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Let sit for at least 4 hours in refrigerator (best if left overnight).
Serve with Triscuits or Wheat Thins.

title: duck and greens
directions: Make 4 inch layer of greens.
Add layer of turnips and bacon. Add another layer of greens and turnips.
Place ducks on top (stuff duck with turnips).
Put bacon around and on top of duck.
Salt well and add 1 cup water.
Cook at 325° for 3 hours and check for doneness.

title: hot doggities
directions: Score surface of hot dogs lightly, spiraling from end to end. Insert wooden skewers for extra eating fun. Roll each hot dog in ketchup or mustard, then coat with bread crumbs.
Place in foil lined shallow baking pan. Do not crowd.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: marinated brussels sprouts
directions: Cut stem ends off Brussels sprouts and boil in about 1-inch of water in medium saucepan about 10 to 12 minutes or until stem ends are tender when pierced.
Drain well and cut Brussels sprouts in half lengthwise.
Add oil and vinegar; toss until well saturated. Stir in green onions and pimentos.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot or store in refrigerator, covered, until next day.

title: tofu-orange almond dessert
directions: Combine orange juice and honey in a small saucepan; simmer, uncovered, until reduced to 3/4 cup.
Stir in orange rind and almond extract.
Combine with tofu squares and tangerine sections. Cover and chill for at least 2 hours prior to serving.
Serve in dessert cups topped with sliced almonds.
Serves 4.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Add hard-cooked eggs if desired.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Place chicken and bay leaf in large Dutch oven and cover with salted water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender. Remove chicken and let cool.
Discard bay leaf.

Bone chicken and cut meat into bite size pieces. Set aside. Remove 1/4 cup chicken broth and set aside. Bring remaining broth to a boil. Break spaghetti into thirds and cook in broth 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Return spaghetti to Dutch oven. Set aside. Saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in butter until tender. Add to spaghetti. Combine cream of mushroom soup and 1/4 cup reserved broth.
Stir into spaghetti mixture. Add tomatoes and chicken. Stir well.
Add seasonings and mix well. Spoon the mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Oil a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square baking pan. Set aside.
Combine the cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt in a small mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Blend the sour cream, eggs and Crisco oil in medium bowl. Add cornmeal mixture, Cheddar cheese, corn and chilies.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 to 15 minutes. Cut in squares and serve warm.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet cook sausage until browned; drain off excess fat. Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and sides to form a crust, seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with hash browns and onion.
Top with cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread with beef
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Heat a large iron skillet and pour half the batter into it.
Layer beef, cheese, onion and peppers over batter.
Pour the remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hominy
directions: Mix milk and sour cream together. Add to drained hominy. Add drained chilies and olives. Layer hominy and cheese in a buttered dish. Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix.
Add soda, vanilla, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Mix well.
Next, add flour, mashed bananas and nuts.
Mix.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes.

title: butterscotch peanut fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine butterscotch pieces, milk and marshmallows.
Stir over medium heat; beat in peanut butter, vanilla and a dash of salt.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator.

title: 4th of july jello ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Divide color into two bowls.
Add sour cream in 1 bowl.
Place sour cream mixture in jello mold.
Place in freezer for 20 minutes.
Once it has set, add 3 tablespoons cold water to 2nd half of mixture.
Pour over 1st layer and let it set for 20 minutes in freezer.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil or melted shortening and milk.
Stir just until all dry ingredients are wet.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch square pan which has been greased, sprinkled with cornmeal and heated.
Cook 20 minutes at 425° or until lightly browned.
Turn out on platter and cut in squares.
(Top is crusty with cornmeal.)

title: meat loaf in the round
directions: Combine the meat, 1 cup cheese, bread crumbs, egg, onion, Worcestershire, salt and pepper; mix well and shape into a ball. Place in shallow 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; pour off the drippings.
Pour tomato sauce over meat.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese; bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with meat tenderizer; slice into 1/2 inch slices.
Saute meat in 3 tablespoons melted butter and oil in skillet for about 30 seconds on each side.
Place browned meat in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine soy sauce, 2 tablespoons butter, lemon juice, sugar, ginger and garlic in small saucepan.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Pour over meat slices. Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 7 to 15 minutes, according to taste.
Serves 6.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Mix all together like regular dough.
Keep the part not used in the refrigerator.
Bake as you would rolls or biscuits.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Divide mixture into 2 balls, then work each ball into long roll, about 1-inch thick.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Slice very thin.
Put pecan half on top of each slice.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 100 rounds.

title: jack's pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Flour roast on all sides and brown in hot oil.
Salt and pepper both sides.
Place in large skillet or roasting pan.
(I use a No. 12 skillet.)
Cut up potatoes and carrots to bite size and place around the roast.
Pour water over meat and vegetables.
Pour 1 package Lipton soup mix over entire preparation.
Cover and place in preheated oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add hot water if needed for additional gravy.

title: hot crunchy chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Top with potato chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can add more or less cornbread as desired.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Roll out on floured board and cut into biscuits.
Brush with melted butter or cooking oil, if desired.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for few days.
Serves 4 dozen biscuits.

title: country ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until lemon color.
Add sugar, a little at a time, then remainder of ingredients.
Pour in freezer and freeze. Makes one gallon.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: no crust fruit custard
directions: Grease glass pie plate. Mix first 6 ingredients. Fold in fruit. Pour into pie plate and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: nancy's dish
directions: In saucepan, mix milk, cheese and flour.
Let heat over medium heat.
Steam potato slices; set aside.
When mixture thickens, add Polish sausage slices, onions and potatoes; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish; let cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: zesty salad
directions: Mix all together and let set in refrigerator overnight. Stir just before serving. Also good with cooked pasta added in.

title: tuna layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, macaroni, cucumbers, tomato, tuna, peas and cheese in 3-quart serving bowl.
Spread dressing over salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: meatloaf puff
directions: In large bowl combine 1 beaten egg and milk.
Stir in soft bread crumbs, onion, 1-1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Add ground beef and mix well.
Pat meat mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2 inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Arrange tomato slices on top of partially baked meat loaf.
Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper.
Cover with American cheese slices.
Beat the egg whites until soft peaks form; set aside.
In small bowl combine sour cream, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Fold beaten egg whites into yolk mixture.
Pour egg mixture over cheese covered meat.
Return to oven and bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8-9.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk to creamed mixture; beat well.
Sift soda and flour together.
Alternate flour and sour cream, adding flour first and last.
Add vanilla, almond extract and salt.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Leave in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add egg and milk.
Beat until smooth. Heat 1 inch of oil to 375°.
Cover bottom opening of funnel. Hold funnel over center of pan.
Begin in center and move outward. Fry 2 minutes or until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel or plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper; add milk. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add 3/4 of the cheese and mix well.
Mix cheese sauce with macaroni; turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell until set, not brown, and let cool.
Fill pie shell with tomato slices, salt, pepper, herbs and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise and grated cheese and spread over tomatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese is lightly browned. Yield:
8 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Do not use electric mixer, use hand to beat.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn oven to 325°, bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake. Makes one pie.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute chopped onion in margarine.
Stem out mushrooms.
Chop stems.
Add to onion.
Mix together until light brown.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: To prepare fruit, select large, firm, tart strawberries.
Wash and drain. Remove caps.

title: heath bar crunch fudge
directions: *You can use the same recipe with any 2 cups of
your favorite candy bar or mini peppermint patties.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together.
Mix in eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix in baking powder, salt, flour and chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Turn into loaf pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch coated with cooking spray.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread 2 tablespoons of ketchup on top of meat loaf.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese (optional) and bake for another 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 7 ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pan; cover with bacon, if you desire.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: spicy cheesy snack
directions: Place chips on a baking sheet.
Spread salsa on top of chips and sprinkle cheese on top of salsa.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute the sugar, milk and butter.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.
Let harden.

title: keftethes tighaniti(fried meatballs)
directions: Soak the bread in warm water.
Remove hard crusts and squeeze out water.
Bread should look like pulp.
Thoroughly combine with all other ingredients.
Form into balls 1 1/2-inch in diameter.* Roll in flour and flatten slightly on either side.
Fry in shallow frypan, turning once or twice.

title: finnish (oven) pancakes(pannukakkua)
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar and beat again. Add flour with salt. Add oleo (use part to grease 13 x 9-inch pan well).
Melt in pan in oven. Last of all, blend in milk that has been slowly heated. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Recipe can be divided in half.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Two eggs, one cup sweet milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, one tablespoon butter, two cups flour; beat the eggs without separating, add milk, salt, melted butter and flour; beat well.
Cut the bananas, as many as you wish to fry, in eight pieces each.
Dip in this batter and fry in deep fat.
When done, if you like sprinkle with granulated sugar and serve hot.

title: french onion soup(crock-pot)
directions: In small skillet, saute onions in butter.
In crock-pot, add water, Worcestershire sauce, salt and onions.
Cover and cook on low for 4 or 5 hours.
Serve in bowl and top with slice of French bread that has been sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled easily.

title: "de-wish-ous" chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Alternately add flour and chocolate syrup, using all in 2 additions.
Add vanilla; pour in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add garlic and tomato puree.
Add chicken and chiles and simmer 10 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Flatten out each biscuit and put hot dog and some cheese in each.
Roll them closed and cook as directed.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, coconut, sugar, nuts and soda together.
Mix oleo, milk and eggs together.
Cut dates and candy.
Roll in flour.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours, until done.

title: captain's chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Put in baking dish.
Pour remaining ingredients over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Melt and heat together all the ingredients. Toss with 2 to 3 quarts of popped popcorn.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for about 20 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Place block of cream cheese on platter.
Pour chili sauce over cream cheese.
Drain crab meat very well.
Arrange crab meat on chili sauce.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: skillet fried corn
directions: Cook bacon crisp.
Drain and crumble.
To drippings add vegetables.
Cover, cook over low heat until just tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Sprinkle bacon over top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet-sour baked beans
directions: Place onions in skillet.
Add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes, covered.
Add onion mixture to beans and add bacon.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for one hour.
Serves 12.

title: icee punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 9 cups warm water.
Dissolve sugar in 4 cups warm water.
Mix everything together and freeze.
Take out of freezer for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Stir with fork to make slushy.
Add 2 to 3 quarts ginger ale.
Serves 50 to 75 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in microwave for 15 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream.
Spread half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased and floured). Sprinkle half cinnamon and sugar mixture over batter.
Spread remaining batter over this.
Top with remaining cinnamon mixture. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While hot, make holes in the cake with fork.
Pour glaze over cake made with powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.

title: potato casserole
directions: Dice and boil the potatoes with the skins on. While they are boiling, melt the cheese in the microwave. Mix the mayonnaise in the cheese.
Put the boiled potatoes in the 9 x 13-inch pan and add salt and pepper.
Pour in the cheese and mayonnaise. Sprinkle with bacon bits and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add onions and green onions for extra flavor.

title: crispy tuna casserole
directions: Drain tuna and set aside.
Melt butter; stir in flour to make smooth paste.
Gradually add milk.
Heat until mixture is slightly thickened.
Reserve a few potato chips for top.
Combine remaining chips with tuna in a bowl.
Gently fold in cream sauce.
Pour mixture into greased 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle reserved crushed chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is lightly brown.
Serves 6.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and 1 stick butter and spread in bottom of pan.
Mix the other stick of
butter, cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar and spread on top.
Top with sliced bananas, crushed pineapple and top with Dream Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Chill.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter. Gradually add sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add soda and salt, mixing well. Gradually add flour until thoroughly blended.

title: cheese dip(like mexico chiquitos)
directions: In top of a double boiler, mix butter and flour to form a paste.
Add rest of ingredients, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and cheese is melted.
Can add more pepper if desired to make hotter.

title: shrimp cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together in a food processor; refrigerate for 1 hour. Roll mixture in a ball. Roll into crushed pecans. Serve with onion crackers.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in heavy gauge 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in morsels until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with walnut halves; press into fudge.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and remove stems from mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly the bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, butter, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Pour 2 tablespoons of oil in bottom of baking dish.
Place mushrooms in pan, stuffed side up.
Pour remainder of oil equally over mushrooms.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
When tops are brown, remove from oven and serve hot.

title: sunday chicken dinner
directions: Mix rice, canned soups and water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours and 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut ends off heavy stalks of broccoli, then cut in about 2-inch lengths.
Steam in basket until tender.
(This may take 10 to 15 minutes.)
Cut the flowerets and stems 3 or 4 inches long and add on top of this.
Cook until tender.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix together the mayonnaise, soup and onion and pour over broccoli.
Grate enough cheese to cover top completely.
Mix stuffing with margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix well sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt, oil, pumpkin, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake on sheet pan at 350° until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix; place in a loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour. Drain and serve.

title: pampered pork chops
directions: Rinse pork chops and place in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Combine other ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes or until done.

title: lemon asparagus chicken
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove and set aside.
Spoon off fat.
In skillet, combine soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink; stir often. Top with lemon slices.

title: carrot-potato puree
directions: Simmer potatoes, carrots and thyme in large saucepan with water to cover for 10 minutes, until fork-tender.
Drain.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook until vegetables are cooked.
Add water as needed.
Freeze leftover for later meal.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper to meat.
Pour off grease.
Add rest of ingredients, except noodles and cheese. Simmer 1 hour on low heat.
Add more tomato sauce if looks dry. Boil noodles in big pan.
Drain.
Spread a little sauce on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer noodles, cheese and sauce until all gone.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Mix egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar, add 1/4 teaspoon salt and beat until fluffy.

Add milk. Whip the cream and add to the egg yolk mixture. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form then add 2 tablespoons sugar. Add to the egg mixture. Put into the mixture. Stir rum into the mixture (to taste).

title: white fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, butter, lemon extract and eggs.
Blend.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed.
Stir in by hand pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Pour into pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Turn on oven to 250°.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Will keep well for up to 6 months if wrapped real good and kept in refrigerator.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.
Pour in 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and freeze.
Serve frozen on lettuce leaves.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, milk, flour and baking powder together.
Pour over melted oleo.
Do not stir. Pour fruit over batter and bake at 350° for 25 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix dry cake mix with oleo, vanilla and eggs in large bowl until smooth.
Add nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Centers should be soft.
If you overbake they will be real hard when cool.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Mix flour, baking powder, shortening and egg; add milk slowly up to 1/2 cup, until right consistency.
Roll out thin; cut in strips.
Drop slowly in boiling chicken broth so boiling does not stop.
Cook until tender.
Leave chunks of chicken in broth, if desired.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Mix 5 ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Melt 1 stick of butter.
Pour over cracker crumbs.
Cover casserole with cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: honolulu fish kebabs
directions: Dissolve 1 teaspoon salt in enough water to cover sliced bananas and soak bananas for about 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Heat oleo in saucepan until melted.
Remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: homemade bread
directions: Combine water, yeast, sugar and oil.
Let work until yeast rises to top of water.
Add flour, salt and eggs.
Knead thoroughly.
Set to rise until double.
Knock down and let rise again.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into 1 to 2-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
(Use a nonstick cookie sheet.)

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In another bowl, mix milk, pudding and whipped topping.
Combine mixtures. Put 1/3 of crushed cookies in bottom of foil-lined clay pot or plastic sand pail.
Add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Top with 1/3 of cookies, then remaining filling.
Top with rest of cookie crumbs before serving.
If desired, add plastic greens or flowers.
Serve with a garden spade.
Makes 10 to 12 large servings.
You can use real flowers.
Cut straw in half; insert flower stem, then stick straw into dirt cake.

title: don's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 4 to 6 hours, stirring more frequently as it gets hotter.

title: butterscotch or chocolate syrup for ice cream
directions: Blend together.
Refrigerate and it is ready to use over ice cream or cake.

title: frozen daiquiri mold
directions: In saucepan, heat 1 cup liquid to a boil.
In a large mixing bowl, dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid.
Add limeade and mayonnaise. Stir until well blended.
Chill until thickened, but not set, approximately 45 minutes.
Fold in pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 6-cup ring mold or an 8 x 8-inch pan. Freeze for 3 hours.
Unmold or cut into cubes.
Garnish with Cool Whip and lime slices.

title: mashed potatoes(serves 100 people)
directions: Peel and pare potatoes.
Cook potatoes until done.
Add all ingredients
and
mix
well.
Using 1/2 cup servings, this will serve 100.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Toss flaked salmon with bread crumbs, onion, cilantro and ginger.
Mix in egg whites.
Form mixture into 8 patties; coat with bread crumbs.
Heat a small amount of oil in a nonstick frying pan.
Saute patties over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with mixed greens with Orange-Ginger Vinaigrette.

title: congealed salad
directions: Let melt on hot stove marshmallows, cream cheese and the salad dressing.
Mix the remaining ingredients in with the first mixture.

title: cheese potatoes in foil
directions: Slice potatoes into a large piece of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Add onion and cheese. Dot with butter.
Wrap loosely and seal well with double folds. Cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Turn occasionally.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
I have found it easier to make this dish using my microwave than before.
It took 3 to 4 different pans.
Cook broccoli in microwave as per directions. Also cook rice in microwave.
Mix broccoli, rice, onion and celery, adding soups and Cheez Whiz.
Turn into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle paprika on top and bake 30 minutes in regular oven at 350°.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: hashed brown potatoes
directions: Prepare and cook whole potatoes.
Drain.
Peel potatoes; shred to make 3 cups.
In a medium skillet, melt butter.
Combine potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Pat into skillet.
Cook over low heat about 15 to 20 minutes or until underside is crisp.
Turn and cook until other side is crisp.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line large casserole dish with uncooked rice and pour 1 cup chicken broth over rice. Dice chicken breasts and spread over rice. Mix soups together with milk and spread over chicken. Melt margarine in 1 cup broth and toss dressing. Spread over soups. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy-does-it meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pat into muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
After cooling, freeze individual loaves in tightly wrapped plastic wrap.
Defrost and microwave for a quick and easy meal.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and pull out stems.
Place caps open side up in greased baking dish.
Chop stems and mix with onion and garlic. Add rest of ingredients.
Place heaping spoonful of mixture in each cap.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until they are tender and tops are brown.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding eggs one at a time.
Bake at 300° in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Start in cold oven!

title: broccoli-ham hot dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain.
Spoon rice into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place broccoli over rice.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of butter over bread crumbs and set aside.
In remaining butter, saute onion until soft; add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and boil until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Add ham and heat through.
Pour over rice and broccoli.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: applesauce oatmeal cookies(no sugar)
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins to plump them; then drain off water and discard.
Mix applesauce, margarine, sweetener, egg and vanilla with raisins.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into 9x13 dish.
Add dry cake mix on top of peaches evenly.
Put slices of butter on top.
Bake at 350 for about 30 minutes until slightly brown.

title: tomato-broccoli quiche
directions: Fix pie crust according to mix directions (or make own).
Cook broccoli and onion in large skillet over medium heat with butter and water just until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Beat cream and eggs together; stir in Swiss cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add broccoli mixture.
Combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs in small bowl.
Assemble quiche.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup Parmesan mixture on bottom of crust.
Dip tomato slices on both sides in Parmesan mixture and arrange half in a layer in the crust. Pour broccoli mixture over tomatoes.
Arrange remaining tomatoes. Sprinkle any remaining cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before cutting.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown beef in large pot.
Drain fat; stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Bring to boil.
Add spaghetti.
Cook 7 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
In bowl mix cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, salt, oregano and garlic powder.
Scoop 1/2 spaghetti mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cottage cheese mixture and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour rest of spaghetti mixture on top. Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
After baking, let stand for 15 minutes.

title: banana frozen salad
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, salt, mayo and lemon juice.
Fold in the pineapple, cherries and nut meats.
Whip 1 cup whipping cream until thick and shiny, but not stiff.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fold in the diced ripe bananas.
Turn into fancy mold; freeze until firm (about 2 hours).
Cut for serving. Garnish with crisp greens.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except dressing and Fritos.
When ready to serve, toss in crushed Fritos and add dressing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: skillet mess
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add tomatoes.
Follow directions on the box for the rice.
Mix together and you have Skillet Mess.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tangerine egg nog
directions: Scald milk in large saucepan.
Beat egg yolks with sugar; stir in about 1 cup hot milk.
Quickly stir mixture into remaining hot milk and cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Chill.
Add tangerine juice concentrate.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: harvest cookies
directions: Blend together the Butter and Sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill dough about 1 hour.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 350 - 375 for 8 - 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: nadine's spaghetti sauce
directions: In Dutch oven or large pot, saute onion in oil.
Add ground beef and stir while it's browning.
Add pepper, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and spaghetti.
Stir well.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Check it occasionally. Add more water if it's too thick.
Serve over cooked spaghetti; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken ovenmeal
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Butter top of chicken.
Spread vegetables (potatoes, onions, then peas and carrots).
Cover with mushroom soup.
Dot with butter.
Add water, salt and pepper. Bake at 400° for 2 hours.

title: banana mallow pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine in skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until coconut is toasted and golden brown (will burn easily).
Press in 9-inch pie plate to form crust. Chill.
Prepare mix as directed for pie filling on package, except using 1 3/4 cups milk.
Cover with waxed paper and chill.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows after cool.
Slice bananas into crust.
Pour filling over bananas.
Chill several hours.

title: chocolate yum yum cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into a mixing bowl.
Set aside. Combine sugar, water, chocolate and margarine in a saucepan; boil 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pour chocolate mixture into dry ingredients. Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost as desired or sift confectioners sugar over the top.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or less (do not preheat oven).

title: famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a

large mixing bowl, cream together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. In another bowl, mix together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Combine wet and dry ingredients. Stir in chocolate chips. With fingers, place golf ball-sized dough portions 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 9 to 10 minutes or just until edges are light brown. Don't overbake. Makes about 30 cookies.

title: sour cream cinnamon coffee cake(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, cream together 1 c. sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla:
beat well.
Blend in sour cream and milk. Add the flour mixture to the batter and mix well.
In a small bowl combine 1/4 c. sugar cinnamon and set aside.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in boiling water.
Add apricot and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Chill until consistency of egg whites.
Then add apricots, crushed pineapple and marshmallows. Chill until firm.
Cook the pineapple and apricot juice (mixed), sugar, flour, butter and egg (beaten).
Cool the mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over the firm jello.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 2-quart 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Combine flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon in medium mixing bowl.
Put in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over apples. Cook at 400° for 30 minutes or at 350° for 45 minutes.
Served with whipped cream.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: You may also use Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar. Add jam and egg yolks, stirring well. Alternate adding part of flour and milk, stirring after each addition until all is added. Beat egg whites until fluffy, then fold them into the cake batter. Cook in 3 (8-inch) cake pans at 325° about 25 minutes, until toothpick in center comes out clean. Cool completely before icing.

title: percolator punch(yield: 22 cups)
directions: In a 30 cup automatic coffee maker, place cloves, cinnamon sticks and salt in basket.
Place juices, water and sugar in bottom.
Plug in and perk.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges.
Combine Cool Whip, jello pistachio pudding and chopped pecans in large bowl.
Add fruit cocktail and oranges.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve as dessert.

title: cherry kuchen
directions: Cream together oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the two mixtures together. It will be thick.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour all but 1 cup of batter into cake pan.
Spread 1 can of cherry pie filling over batter.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls over cherry topping.
Bake 40 minutes, or until tests done, at 350°.

title: pork loin
directions: Dip pork loin in soy sauce and rub in with your hands.
Brown meat lightly in a roasting pan.
Boil sauce ingredients in a separate pan that is large enough to hold pork for further cooking after the browning process.
After sauce comes to a boil, add meat and stir often to prevent scorching.
Cook until transparent juices run from meat when testing fork is inserted.
Remove meat and allow to cool before slicing.
Allow remaining liquid to reduce in volume and thicken to be served as a sauce/gravy for pork loin.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Blend 4 ounces cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives or onions and pimiento.
Saute onion in butter prior to putting it into the mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into four rectangles.
Seal perforations with finger.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center and seal edges.
Brush tops with melted margarine.
Dip in 3/4 cup crushed croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 squares.

title: play dough
directions: Cook in a saucepan on medium heat until it forms a ball.

title: buttermilk date pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, spices and salt in saucepan; blend thoroughly.
Gradually stir in buttermilk and egg yolks.
Add dates.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Cool slightly.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown or chill pie thoroughly and serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli-peanut casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, margarine, salt and a small amount of water in a pan. Bring to a boil; cover and cook 6 to 8 minutes or just until broccoli is fork-tender. Drain.
Combine the broccoli and onion with 2 cans of soup, 1 cup cheese, garlic salt, Accent, 1/2 cup peanuts and the mushrooms.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with extra cheese, cracker crumbs and remaining 1/2 cup peanuts. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix milk and vinegar together.
Set aside.
Melt margarine. Add sugar and cream well.
Add vanilla.
Then add eggs.
(Be sure to beat eggs well as this makes the pies better than your usual pies.)
Add milk.
Stir in coconut and mix well. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake on lowest rack for 40 minutes at 350°. This will serve 8 (each pie).

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break up cake to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve jello in water; add frozen berries, partially set.
Pour over cake.
Chill until firm.
In double broiler, cook egg yolks, sugar and milk until slightly thick; soften gelatin in cold water.
Add to egg yolk mixture.
Let cool.
Fold whipped topping and stiffly beaten egg whites into the cooled egg yolk mixture.
Add vanilla and salt.
Spread over berry mixture.
Chill until set.

title: tres leches cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sift flour and baking powder together and set aside. Cream butter and 1 cup of sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs and 1/2 teaspoon of the vanilla extract; beat well.
Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture 2 tablespoons at a time, mixing until well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done when tested with a toothpick.
Pierce cake many, many times with a fork.
Whisk together the whole milk, evaporated milk and condensed milk until well mixed.
Pour about 2 cups at a time over cooled cake, letting mixture absorb into cake until all milk mixture is used.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Whip whipping cream, 1 1/3 cups sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla together until thick.
Spread over the top of the cake.
Be sure and keep cake refrigerated.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook with beef until tender.
Add stewed tomatoes, rice, water and seasonings.
Stir frequently until a thick consistency.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese on top of mixture until melted.
Serve with warm French bread.

title: raspberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place washed berries in the bottom of a well-greased deep dish. Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk and pour evenly over the fruit. Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar on top of batter. Pour 1 cup boiling water over all. Do not stir. Bake about 1 hour or until crusty and lightly browned. Serve warm with ice cream or cool and top with whipped topping.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain green beans and corn.
Add cream of chicken soup and water chestnuts (drained and diced).
Stir in celery, onion and shredded cheese.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine and stir in crushed Ritz crackers.
Place on top of vegetables.
(I use Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix instead of crackers.)
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: crusty parmesan biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cheese.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine milk and egg and add to dry mixture, mixing just until moistened.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water until all the water is gone.
Combine all other ingredients, add raisins.
Shape dough into small balls. Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan until desired thickness.

title: fudgy chocolate layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour two 9 - inch round pans.
In a saucepan; melt butter and chocolate, stirring over low heat.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in a large bowl of electric mixer.
Add chocolate mixture, buttermilk and eggs.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute; increase speed to high and beat until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain hearts and chop.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Add Parmesan cheese and a big dash of garlic powder.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.
This dip may also be served cold.
(Great with Ritz crackers.)

title: green vegetable salad
directions: Mix together all vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow pan.
Place a slice of onion on each pork chop.
Roast in very hot oven, at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: best ever fish fillets
directions: Rinse fish; pat dry with paper towel.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Brush with milk.
Combine crumbs and ginger. Sprinkle crumb mixture and almonds over fish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in a 450° oven for 6 to 12 minutes (until fish flakes easily).

title: ham and bacon fried rice
directions: Stir-fry bacon, garlic, onion and ham.
Drain.
Add oil and scramble eggs.
Add spring onion, peas and carrots, bean sprouts and pea pods.
Fry for 2 minutes.
Add steamed rice and the rest of the seasonings.
Fry for 5 minutes.
Top with sesame oil and serve.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix well with mixer.
Form into 2 or 3 balls.
Roll ball in 1/2 chili powder and 1/2 paprika or roll in chopped nuts.
Can be frozen for future use.

title: quick grape juice
directions: Place cup of grapes in quart jar along with 1/2 cup sugar. Cover with boiling water.
Make sure water is boiling.
Turn jars upside down until they seal.
Let set 10 to 14 days.
Makes delicious grape jelly.

title: diabetic grape spread
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water. Heat grape and lemon juice. Bring to a boil and simmer gently for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add gelatin and artificial sweetener. Stir to dissolve. Pour carefully into 2 hot, clean 1/2 pint jars. Cover lightly until cooled, then tighten lids and store in refrigerator.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter; put into 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Brown in oven at 350°.
Cool.

title: holiday hunks
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and baking soda and mix.
Add flour and spices and mix.
Stir in nuts and fruits. Drop by teaspoon size hunks onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with celery sticks or your favorite cracker.

title: hawaiian blueberry pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Use 3/4 of pie dough for a good crust and 1/4 for extra flute on rim.
If berries are frozen, allow to thaw.
Place in 9-inch pie shell.
Dot with butter and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Bake in 3 round pans at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool layers.
Frost layers; refrigerate for 24 hours before cutting.
Mix the last 4 ingredients for frosting.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour. Prick top of cake with a fork, then add icing.

title: chicken dressing delite
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter and saute onion until tender. Add milk and soup.
Bring to a bubble.
Put chicken in mixture and cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Put in large oblong pan and in a separate bowl pour the stuffing mix and make a paste with chicken broth and water.
Spread on top of chicken and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with cheese and bake additional 5 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Toss cooked noodles with butter and spread in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sauerkraut and juice over noodles.
Next, spread corned beef.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, ketchup and dill weed.
Spread over top of corned beef.
Cover with foil.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove.
Add cheese and cover with crushed crackers.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins that are 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Puree the sweet potatoes in a food processor or blender.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs and sweet potatoes.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients alternately by hand with the milk and chopped nuts and raisins, mixing just until blended.
Do not overmix.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in the large bowl of your electric mixer.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased angel food cake pan and bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes, or until center tests done.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap with foil or plastic wrap to keep fresh.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Combine sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla; cream until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: harvest feast potatoes
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: souperburger
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onion and mustard.
Cook and stir until onion is done.
Add soup and 1/2 can water.
Cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over bread or mashed potatoes.

title: date nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and pinch of salt until stiff.
Gradually add other ingredients.
Bake in buttered pie plate 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: finger-poppin' fried chicken strips
directions: Pat chicken pieces dry.
Make a paste of flour, salad dressing mix, lemon juice and butter.
Stir chicken strips into the paste to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate one hour or more.
About one hour before serving, heat oil 1/2 inch deep in a large skillet and preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pancake mix, paprika, sage and pepper in a plastic or paper bag.
Moisten the marinated chicken strips with milk.
Drain off any excess and reserve.
Turn chicken into bag of seasoned pancake mix.
Shake to coat well.
Fry chicken strips in hot oil, stirring to separate, for 1 to 2 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Spread chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle lightly with reserved milk.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Uncover, raise temperature to 400° and bake 5 minutes more to crisp chicken, basting once more with milk, if desired.
Let cool slightly before serving.
Makes 4 hors d'oeuvres or 2 entree portions.

title: daddy hatcher's strawberry pudding(a variation of banana pudding)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and cook over double boiler until thickened.
Layer strawberries and Nilla wafers alternately in a casserole dish.
Pour pudding over layered Nilla wafers and strawberries.
Top with meringue and brown slightly in oven/broiler.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute celery, onion, carrots and olive oil.
Stir chicken broth, diced potatoes and cayenne pepper.
Bring to boil; simmer until potatoes are done.
Serve with cheese and bacon bits.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Mix together salsa and chili sauce.
Spread cream cheese over platter or plate.
Top with salsa mixture. Then put
layer of sour cream.
Next top with 2 cheeses.
Garnish with sliced black olives and green chilies.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Cook zucchini in butter until tender.
Place in shallow pan. Make dressing.
Add remaining ingredients to zucchini and spoon dressing on top.
Bake at 350 for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute parsley, onion and garlic in oil. When golden, add 3 cups water and tomato sauce.
Soak rice in water.
Drain out the water and add rice to skillet.
Leave, uncovered, and cook until most of the water is absorbed.
Put cover on and let cook for additional 10 to 15 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Put chips in double boiler until melted.
Place condensed milk, coconut and pecans together.
Mix well.
Add to chocolate. Put in buttered dish and refrigerate.
Cut into small squares.

title: baked bombay chicken(yields 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat baking sheet with cooking spray.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Brown pork chops and place in casserole dish.
Dump kidney beans on top.
Place green pepper strips on top next.
Then pour chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar over pepper strips.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake approximately 1/2 hour more.
Mixture will thicken as it sets (can add more brown sugar if you like).

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Spray 11 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Break up bread into small pieces. Cover bottom of pan with bread. Cook sausage and pour over bread. Place onion, pepper and mushrooms on top of sausage. Sprinkle with cheese. Beat eggs, milk and mustard. Pour over top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. This is good to make the night before and put in the refrigerator, then bake for company the next morning.

title: zucchini fries
directions: Cut the zucchini and squash into fries about 2 inches long and 1/2 inch thick.
In large no stick frying pan over medium heat, saute the veggies in oil for 5 minutes or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with basil.
Low-fat.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together until the consistency of coarse meal; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves a lot of folks.
(This is a double recipe; use half the ingredients for 5 to 6 servings.)

title: sweet minglers
directions: In large bowl, melt chocolate at High for 1 minute in microwave.
Stir and heat an additional 30 seconds at High or until melted.
Stir in peanut butter and peanuts.
Pour mixture over cereal.
Place 4x sugar in 2-gallon storage bag.
Add coated cereal to sugar and close bag.
Toss bag until cereal is thoroughly coated with sugar.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: spiced tea
directions: Dip tea and spices into one gallon hot water until colored and seasoned.
Sweet to taste, while hot, with honey.
When cool, add juices.

title: stromboli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Unroll crust onto greased cookie sheet. Spread pizza sauce onto pizza crust.
Add a small amount of cheese, then add toppings.
After toppings have been added, cover with cheese.
Roll crust from one end to another.
Spread butter or spray Pam cooking oil over the top and place in oven approximately 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Ovens vary so watch after about 7 to 8 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter, poppy seeds, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onions together.
Spread tops and bottoms of rolls with creamed mixture.
Add sliced ham and Swiss cheese slices.
Close rolls and slice into individual roll servings.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 1 minute, then add oats, and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in blender.
Pour in greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Must use big pie pan, 10-inches or more.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and slice potatoes.
In a medium bowl, put layer of potatoes, then layer of mayonnaise, sour cream, celery salt and horseradish that has been mixed together, ending with sour cream mixture on top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together over low heat; let cool to lukewarm.
Fold in the Cool Whip that has been left sitting out of refrigerator (not quite room temperature).
Pour into cooled pie crust and chill.

title: flora raper's hypocrite pie
directions: In a saucepan, cover the apples with water and cook until tender and water is absorbed.
Season with sugar and cinnamon to taste.
When apple mixture is cooled, spoon into bottom of pie shell about 1/2 inch thick.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Stir until a soft dough forms and pat over bottom of 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: oven meatballs for two
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into balls.
Place in small baking dish and bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes.

title: pork chops-potatoes-tomatoes bake
directions: Brown the pork chops.
Peel and slice the potatoes and chop the onion.
Place both in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Place browned chops on top.
Place peeled tomatoes on top of pork chops, using juice also.
Add small amount of water to pan. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and return to oven for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: cream of mushroom soup(french)
directions: Slice enough mushrooms to measure 1 cup.

Chop remaining mushrooms. Cook and stir sliced mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of butter in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat until golden brown. Remove mushrooms with slotted spoon. Cook chopped mushrooms and onion in remaining butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour and salt. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in chicken broth and water.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in half and half and sliced mushrooms.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Core and pare apples.
Cook
until
tender
in
a syrup made with the sugar, water, candies and
a
drop or two of red food coloring.
Chill and serve around meat or as a salad.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, chocolate squares, cold water, salt and butter. Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to sugar mixture and mix. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: grandmothers tea cakes
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Mix with eggs.
Pour in vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Gradually mixing with sugar and egg mixture.
Put salt in milk and mix with other mixture.
Roll thin and bake at 350°.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook sausage and onion with oregano until done.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add soups and water.
Combine meat mixture and cooked noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart shallow baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, rice, egg, onion and seasonings.
Remove cabbage core and wilt in boiling water for 5 minutes until pliable. Drain and cool slightly.
Separate leaves and place 2 tablespoons meat mixture on each and roll up.
Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole and line with extra leaves and sauerkraut.
Place pigs on top. Cover with soup and water mixture, then rest of cabbage leaves. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 400°.
May be cooked ahead and re-warmed for later use.

title: banana split pie
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, confectioners sugar, milk and crushed pineapple.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Cover the top with 2 bananas, sliced and top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons mix per cup of water.
Makes 4 cups of mix or 60 cups of tea.

title: pork chops in onion sauce(german style)
directions: Season pork with salt and pepper.
Coat with flour.
Heat oil in heavy frypan.
Add chops; fry each side 3 minutes.
Add onions; cook 5 minutes, turning chops once.
Pour in beer and broth; cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove chops to preheated platter. Season sauce to taste.
Blend cornstarch with small amount cold water.
Stir into sauce; cook until thick.
Pour over pork.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add next 6 ingredients in order given, spreading evenly over pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger steaks
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
except
the
soup.
Make
into patties and brown in a
skillet with a small amount of grease. Place patties into a
casserole dish.
Pour mushroom soup over them and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: penne with vegetables
directions: In a small sauce pan, saute onions & garlic in olive oil until browned.
In large sauce pan, melt butter.
Add flour & stir.
Slowly add Half & Half and milk, simmer, stirring constantly till thickened.
Add cheese & seasonings.
Stir until cheese melts and add tomatoes, spinach and onion mixture.
Heat through.
Pour over warmed pasta toss and serve.

title: company wild rice
directions: Stir rice into 1 1/2 cups boiling water and 1/2 teaspoon salt in heavy saucepan.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, or until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in butter in large skillet for 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, cream and spices.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice. Place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour half of cake batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of nut mixture (margarine, walnuts and brown sugar) over batter. Pour remaining batter in pan.
Sprinkle remainder of nut mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
If it comes out clean, remove from oven.
Serves 12 or more.
Can freeze.

title: wassail
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Turn on high until hot, then turn to low.
Refrigerate to keep fresh.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and jell.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening seasoned with thyme. Remove chicken
and pat with paper towels.
Rinse skillet.
Stir in soup, water, pepper and onions.
Add chicken.
Cover, leaving slit for steam to escape.
Cook over low heat 45 to 60 minutes to desired tenderness.
Turn chicken and stir gravy occasionally. Add more water if necessary.
Serve over noodles or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crisp chicken breast
directions: Dredge chicken breasts in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Put Crisco in cast-iron skillet.
Melt over medium heat on stove. Place chicken breast in skillet and cook until golden brown.
Turn over and cook with lid on for another 20 minutes.
Remove lid. Cook about 5 minutes more.
Serve at once.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat oil and sugar well.
Add carrots and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: uncooked chili sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes and onions, mix with the salt.
Put this mixture in a cloth bag and drain overnight.

title: "cherry gook"
directions: Fold together pie filling, pineapple and condensed milk; add Cool Whip.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch container.
Place in freezer. Remove from freezer 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute
onions
in
butter for 15 minutes.
Layer 1/2 in casserole
dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and crumbled Ritz
crackers.
Repeat
layers of onions, Parmesan cheese and crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti a la buchanan
directions: Fry the green pepper and onion in lard.
Add ground beef. After meat is done, add spaghetti sauce and bring to a boil. Serve over spaghetti.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven
Combine crumbs and butter.
Pat firmly on bottom
of
9-inch
spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until
fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk until smooth. Add eggs and
vanilla
and
mix
well.
In
small
bowl,
toss together 1/2 cup chips with flour to coat and stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into
prepared
pan.
Sprinkle
remaining chips evenly over top. Bake 1
hour or until cake springs back when lightly
touched. Cool
to room temperature and chill.
After it has cooled, remove side of pan.
Garnish as desired.

title: lazy day bars
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sugar, butter and water.
Stir until smooth.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: center soup
directions: Place water and bouillon cubes in pot; cut vegetables into bite size pieces and place in pot.
Bring to a boil, then cover. Cook until vegetables are near desired consistency.
Add egg noodles; simmer until noodles are tender.
Season to taste.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook all of the vegetables together until tender.
Melt the butter in a pan.
Blend in the flour and cook until bubbly. Remove from heat.
Add the milk and place it back on the heat and cook until thick.
Add to hot vegetables and add the cheese. Enjoy!

title: mini-reubens(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Reheats well in microwave.
Serve on party rye.

title: buttermilk pie(delicious)
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend well.
Preheat oven to 425°.
When you put the pie in oven, turn oven to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Test for doneness by inserting knife in the center. Delicious.

title: mock barbecue
directions: Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, pineapple and vanilla. Sift flour and soda. Add to egg mixture; mix well. Add nuts.
Place batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool. Frost with frosting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine in saucepan and boil until thick all ingredients except strawberries.
Let cool.
Add strawberries.
Put in 9-inch baked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup and water in a saucepan over low heat. Stir until sugar is dissolved, then cook without stirring to 255°. Remove from heat and pour, beating constantly, in a fine stream into stiffly beaten egg whites. Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss. Add vanilla and pecans. Drop quickly from tip of spoon onto waxed paper in individual peaks. Amount: Makes 8 dozen pieces.

title: spicy chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out a hard roll and fill with mixture.
Place on baking sheet and put in 350° oven until cheese is melted and rolls are crisp.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips in microwave for 2 minutes. Put cereal in a bowl and pour chocolate over it. Mix well. Put powdered sugar in a brown paper bag.
Pour Chex mixture into bag and shake up. Then eat.

title: savory grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large glass baking dish.
In a bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well blended.
Reserve 1/2 cup marinade for basting during grilling.
Pour remaining marinade over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour, turning chicken once. Grill chicken until done to your liking.

title: broccoli-ham quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in whipping cream, ham, cheeses, broccoli, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into shell.
Bake 40 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Cook celery in salted water until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan; add mushrooms and simmer 5 minutes.
Add onion to this mixture.
Add the flour and blend, then the milk and cream; simmer until it has thickened.
Add cooked celery mix and season with pepper and more salt, if desired.
Heat and serve.
A dash of whipped cream may be added.

title: baked apples
directions: Cook apples in all ingredients until tender and about 1/2 of water has boiled away.
Pour syrupy apples in baking dish; bake, uncovered, in oven for 2 hours at 350°.

title: award-winning potato-lover's salad
directions: Place potatoes whole and unpeeled in vegetable steamer, covered, over boiling water for 20 minutes or until almost tender. While potatoes are steaming, prepare broccoli, greens and dressing. Remove from heat and cut into 1/2-inch cubes (peeling is optional).
Place in a large bowl and set aside.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Pour butter over the potatoes and toss well. Add salt and paprika.
Mix well.
Place potatoes and toss on cookie sheet.
Place at highest shelf position in preheated broiler. Broil for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms and set aside.
Start to brown meat in a large skillet; add mushrooms, rice, onion and pepper. Continue browning until rice is lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, water and seasoning.
Turn into a 3-quart casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove cover for last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth, then add peanut butter.
Keep mixing together.
Add Cool Whip, then pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple noodle ring
directions: Cook noodles.
Add all ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: good cake
directions: Mix together and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cake
directions: Mix water, oatmeal and butter in bowl.
Let stand for 20 minutes, then add the white sugar, brown sugar, eggs, soda, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch) for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: brown betty
directions: Combine crumbs and butter. Arrange in layers in greased baking dish. First crumbs, then apples, having crumbs for top layer. Dot with additional butter and bake in 350 degree oven for about 20 minutes. Serve with light cream.

title: brie and walnut filled phyllo
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter.
Add pork and saute, stirring and breaking meat into small pieces.
Add water and seasonings and cook for 30 minutes.
If mixture looks watery, add a little cornstarch.
Chill.

title: impossible brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish.
Beat all ingredients in blender until smooth, except nuts.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Add flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs until creamy.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake in moderate oven until crispy done (about 350° for 15 minutes).
Test with toothpick.

title: swiss cheese and ham biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut rolls in half (do not pull apart). Mix by hand in bowl butter, poppy seed, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion until creamy.
Spread the mixture evenly on all 4 halves of the rolls.
Put ham and cheese on the bottom until all are covered.
Put tops back on.
Put in oven until cheese is melted, then cool and cut into squares.

title: communion bread
directions: Put
plain
flour
in
large mixing bowl.
Add water as needed to form ball of dough.
Roll onto floured surface, very thin. Bake
at
for 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not brown, just cook long enough to lightly color.
Cut into small pieces.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Place rice in bottom of baking dish; arrange chicken on top. Combine the soup, green pepper, water, soy sauce, ginger and 1/2 can onion rings and pour over chicken and rice.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Top with remaining 1/2 can onion rings. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: rich chocolate pudding
directions: Stir sugar and cornstarch together in a 1-quart glass measure. Gradually stir in milk until blended. Add chopped chocolate. Microwave, uncovered, at High power for 5 minutes.
