Whisk thoroughly to blend chocolate. Microwave at High power until boiling and thickened, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in vanilla and salt. Pour into 4 custard cups. Let stand until cooled.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over broccoli, turning a couple of times.
Marinate 24 hours or up to 48 hours.
(After that, it gets mushy!)

title: linguine with white clam sauce(prep time:  10 minutes.  cooking:  14 minutes)
directions: Cook the linguine according to package directions, omitting the salt.
Rinse with cold water; drain and set aside.
Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a heavy 10-inch skillet over moderate heat for 1 minute; add onion and garlic and cook, uncovered, until onion is soft, about 5 minutes.
Blend in the flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Add the wine and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the clam juice and chicken broth and cook, stirring, 4 minutes longer.
Stir in the clams and cheese.
Add the reserved linguine and cook 1 minute longer, tossing well until heated through.
Mix in parsley and serve. Serves 4.

title: placerville angel cake
directions: Take 1 pound soda box, cut 2 1/2 inches from bottom and fill with sugar.
Sift sugar 7 times.
Fill your "measuring box" with flour and 1 teaspoon of cream of tartar.
Sift this mixture 7 times.
Separate the 12 eggs and beat egg whites with a metal whisk into a stiff froth.
Beat into the egg whites the sugar and flour, a little at a time (3 spoonfuls of sugar, then flour) until all is gone.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: muddy buddies
directions: In a large microwave bowl, melt chocolate chips on High for 1 minute.
Stir and heat for 30 seconds more, if necessary.
Stir in peanut butter.
Gently stir in cereal.
Put powdered sugar in a 2-gallon zip bag, then add cereal mixture and toss gently until coated.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Arrange in baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and spices.
Spread cake mix evenly over top. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess cake
directions: Mix together 1 egg, melted butter and cake mix.
Put this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: b.l.t. salad
directions: Mix with mayonnaise, sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with chopped tomatoes and lettuce.
This is good for days.
I make it sometimes without lettuce and use it for sandwich spread, especially for ham sandwiches.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Stir flour, soda and salt.
Add oil and sugar substitute.
Mix well.
Beat eggs and rest of ingredients into mixture.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch loaf pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jane's taco dip
directions: Spread in circle.
Top with lettuce, shredded sharp cheese, tomato, black olives, onion, etc.
Dip.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Heat corn syrup to boiling; add butter and heat to boiling again.
Cool slightly and add remaining ingredients.
Dough should be stiff.
Chill overnight.
Make a long roll and cut off in small pieces about every 1/2-inch or so.
Place about 1/2 to 3/4-inch diameter on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake as needed.
Keep dough chilled.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes; don't overbake. It should be firm when tested with finger.

title: hawaiian ice cream pie
directions: Mix butter with coconut.
Press firmly against bottom and sides of 9-inch pan and toast in 350° oven 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool thoroughly.
Spoon or scoop ice cream into shell allowing scoops to remain in lumps.
Don't spread.
Place in freezer.
Mix strawberries with pineapple chunks.
Spoon fruit over pie when ready to serve.

title: noodles
directions: Mix flour, eggs and salt.
Add 1 tablespoon water until dough forms ball.
Knead 10 minutes; cover.
Rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough in 4 parts.
Roll.
Cut 1/4 or 1/8 inch.
Dry 2 hours.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Bring 7 cups of water
and sugar to a boil; let cool.
Boil 2 more cups of water; let cool with tea bags in it.
When this is cool, add frozen lemonade, frozen orange juice and whiskey. Freeze.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all except chicken, cheese and Doritos and heat.
In casserole dish, layer alternately the Doritos, chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding with lemon sauce
directions: Tear bread into small pieces (you should have 4 cups). Combine bread, milk and dates.
Let stand 15 minutes or until bread is softened, stirring often.
Beat together eggs, sugar, melted butter, vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir into bread mixture until blended.
Turn into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm with Lemon Sauce.
Garnish with apple chunks and sweet woodruff or mint leaves, if desired. Makes 9 servings.

title: potato bacon chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in an 8-quart pan.
Pour off all but enough fat to saute onion and celery.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add potatoes, carrots, ham, parsley and crumbled bacon to sauteed onion and celery.
Add enough water just to cover.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat to simmer until vegetables are tender.
Mix together soup, sour cream and milk and add to pot. Season to taste and heat only to serving temperature.
Do not boil.
Serve with French bread on a cool day.
Can also be made in crock-pot.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: lemon sirloin steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; place meat in plastic bag in a shallow dish.

title: dessert
directions: Mix together spices, vanilla and sour cream.
Slice up celery and apples and combine with raisins and walnuts in sour cream sauce.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Bake 4 whole breasts until done.
In 3-quart casserole, layer 1/2 of each of vegetables and chestnuts.
Add soup (heat if it's to be frozen); add all the chicken in the middle.
Add remaining half of vegetables and chestnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes plus, covered.
Uncover and top with onions and cheese.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with soy sauce.
Serves 8.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Mix boiling water and cocoa to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until blended well.
Pour into 2 round pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spiced apple revel loaf
directions: Peel apple rings; mash with a fork.
Add brown sugar, the cinnamon (1/4 teaspoon), nutmeg and ginger.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, cream butter and granulated sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Thoroughly stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread one-third of the batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Drop one-third of the apple mixture by tablespoons onto batter.
Repeat layers to make 3 layers of each, ending with apple mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: zucchini-orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of two 8 x 4 or 9 x 5 loaf pans.
In large bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually.
Stir in oil, 2/3 cup orange juice and zucchini.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Stir in remaining bread ingredients; mix well.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool slightly in small bowl.
Blend glaze ingredients and spread over warm bread.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake as directed on package in a 9 X 13 pan. Prepare Dream Whip.
While cake is still hot pour juice from pineapple over top.
Mix milk and pudding mix together; add to prepared Dream Whip.
Spread over cake and sprinkle with coconut.

title: water chestnut and pineapple roll-ups
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: cinnamon zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Sift corn meal, salt and soda together over cracklings.
Mix well.
Combine buttermilk and beaten egg.
Stir into corn meal mixture.
Pour into a hot, greased bread pan.
Bake at 450° for about 25 minutes or until brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar and continue beating.
Add canned milk and vanilla flavoring.

title: weber grill sun jerky
directions: Note:
Need brown paper bag and covered grill and briquets.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind onion, cabbage, green tomatoes, green peppers, red peppers and celery.
You can use food processor.
Add salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture.
Spread on wax paper.

title: golden harvest mold
directions: Heat 2 cups cider or juice to boiling.
Add gelatin and dissolve.
Stir in remaining cider or juice and lemon juice. Chill until partially set.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into six cup mold or individual cups.
Chill until set.
Garnish with additional apple slices and walnuts.
Serves 8 to 10.
Goes good with pork, poultry or fish.
Nice for Halloween.

title: cranberry-orange sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Place over medium heat, and bring to a boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat to low, and simmer, stirring often, until thick (about 10 minutes). Remove from heat and cool.
Serve warm or cold.

title: herbed turkey breast
directions: Put turkey in crockpot.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush over turkey.
Cover.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 5 to 6 hours.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add flour, Grape-Nuts, milk and lemon juice.
Beat egg yolks and add to preceding mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold into preceding mixture.
Bake in a pan of water at 375°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar, molasses and shortening together.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until well blended, then add boiling water and beat until smooth.
The batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan, 9 x 14-inch, and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Heat oil; saute chicken.
Add celery, mushrooms, salt and soy sauce.
Stir 2 minutes.
Cover and cook 5 minutes on medium-low heat.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir into chicken until it thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese and potato salad
directions: Place eggs in saucepan; cover with cold water.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat to just below simmering.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes. Run cold water over eggs until cool.
Remove shells.
Chop eggs. Meanwhile in bowl combine salad dressing, vinegar, onion and mustard.
Add celery and cottage cheese; mix well.
Gently fold in potatoes and eggs.

title: velvet corn soup
directions: In small bowl, beat the egg whites with a fork until frothy. Then beat in the milk.
Have the corn, egg whites mixture, chicken stock, salt, cornstarch mixture and crab meat within easy reach. In a 2-quart saucepan, bring the chicken stock to a boil over high heat.
Add the corn and salt, stirring constantly, bring to boil again.
Give the cornstarch mixture a quick stir to recombine it and pour it into the soup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the soup has thickened and becomes clear.
Turn off heat and immediately pour in the egg white mixture, stirring only once. Quickly pour the hot soup into a tureen or individual bowls and sprinkle with the crab meat.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into butter mixture.
Spread batter in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add soup, tomato paste and mushrooms.
Thin mixture with the water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Just before serving, blend in sour cream.
Serve hot over noodles. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick cube steak
directions: Lay raw cube steak in pan.
May brown if desired.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over steak.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Pour over steak.
Bake at 300° for 2-3 hours.

title: corned beef cheese logs
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with milk until smooth.
Blend in Worcestershire sauce and pepper sauce.
Flake corned beef into cheese mixture.
Refrigerate 1 or 2 hours.
Remove and divide in half.
Shape into 2 logs 1 1/2 x 7-inches.
Sprinkle parsley on waxed paper.
Roll logs in parsley to coat evenly.
Wrap well in plastic wrap and chill thoroughly.
Serve with sesame crackers or Melba crackers.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine mushroom soup and asparagus water and heat.
Layer in Pyrex dish twice the cracker crumbs, asparagus, eggs, soup mixture and cheese.
Put pats of butter and crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocoa-banana muffinettes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 30 miniature muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with no-stick cooking spray. Combine first six ingredients; mix well.
Add combined bananas, milk, margarine, egg whites and vanilla, mixing just until moistened.
Fill prepared cups almost full.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let muffins stand a few minutes.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: blue-cheese-roquefort salad dressing
directions: Run
the onion through the meat grinder followed by the cheeses.
(blender) Place in mixing bowl, add rest of ingredients. Mix
well.
It's
best when made the day before, use so flavors can
marry.
If
the dressing is too thick, thin with buttermilk.

title: arizona chili con carne y frijoles
directions: Sort the beans, looking carefully for any stones or dirt clods and removing them.
Soak the beans!
This is the first and most important rule for good beans.

title: whiskey seed pound cake(all ingredients at room temperature.)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Use electric mixer (much mixing needed).
At high speed cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and nutmeg.
Dredge orange peel with a little of the flour.
Turn mixer on low speed and gradually add remaining flour.

title: chow chow
directions: Let stand overnight, then drain, then put 1-quart vinegar, 1/4 cup pickling spice and 1 3/4 cups sugar.
Boil until tender, then put in jars and seal.

title: cheesy sausage muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center.
Combine eggs and milk; add to sausage mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin pans, filling three-fourths full.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup and eggs together.
Add onion, mayonnaise, cheese and broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown on top.

title: raffetto - chutney
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on your favorite crackers.
Will last a long time in the refrigerator.

title: basic salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss well.
Use this fresh salsa at room temperature immediately or keep in the refrigerator for up to two days.
Serves 4.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all ingredients.
Chill and form into a ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: greek french bread
directions: Blend together oleo and mayonnaise.
Add rest of ingredients and blend.
Split a loaf of bread lengthwise and spread mixture equally on both sides.
Close bread and rewrap.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. You can reopen bread and distribute mixture again before baking if you like.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven. This can be frozen.

title: pleasin' pea salad
directions: Combine peas, celery, cheese, olives and onions in a medium size mixing bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients until smooth. Add to the pea mixture. Stir to combine. Serve chilled. Serves 4.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Mix lemonade, cream of coconut, pineapple juice and vodka. Freeze overnight (an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan works best). Scoop into glass and pour Squirt over.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Slice strawberries and mix with sugar to taste, set aside. Beat eggs with mixer, add sugar, flour, vanilla and boiling water. (This will be a thin mixture.)
Pour into 2 lightly greased and floured round pans.
Bake in 350 degree oven until done, cool. Place first cake layer on serving plate and spread with half of strawberries, followed by half of Cool Whip.
Place second cake layer on top of first and spread with remaining strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: potato and spinach layer
directions: Place the potatoes in a saucepan of boiling, lightly salted water and cook for 5 minutes or until just tender.
Drain and leave to cool slightly.
Place the spinach in a saucepan with just the water from the washing and cook for 4 to 5 minutes or until softened.
Drain excess water.
Add nutmeg, seasoning and yogurt. Place half the spinach at the base of a shallow, flameproof dish. Top with a layer of potatoes, using half the potato slices.
Repeat the layers, making sure spinach is completely covered by potatoes. Season the top layer and brush with oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and place in a preheated oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes to brown.
Makes 6 servings.
Immediately garnish with fresh herb sprigs.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix and spread with spatula to wafer thin thickness.
Pour egg white (unbeaten) on mixture.
Spread with fingers, pour off excess.
Sprinkle cup of pecans over top.
Bake at 350°; cut while hot.

title: rye bread pizza
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion; drain.
Add salt, pepper and Italian seasonings to taste.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir until melted.
Spread mixture on rye bread slices.
Cool and freeze.

title: mae's vegetable salad
directions: Pour all vegetables into a bowl; add in chopped onion, bell pepper and celery.
Mix well.
In saucepan, heat sugar, vinegar and oil until hot; pour over vegetables.
Place in refrigerator, covered; chill overnight.

title: crunch pound cake
directions: Mix together well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then turn down to 325° for 30 more minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute in oil 2 cups of ham, onion and celery.
Add and simmer water, potatoes, bay leaf and salt.
When potatoes are soft, remove from heat and let cool slightly while making white sauce.

title: strawberry surprise muffins
directions: Preheat oven as directed on muffin mix package.
In a small bowl, prepare muffin mix as directed.
Spoon 1/2 of batter into prepared muffin cups.
Top with 1 tablespoon of preserves.
Bake as directed.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Cool.
Blend in 1/4 cup mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Add prepared mustard to taste.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add onion and garlic; cook until browned.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, oregano and sugar.
Cover; simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese and Parmesan; stir until cream cheese has melted and is well combined.
Serve warm with Fritos.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with melted butter.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix softened Philadelphia cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Beat whipping cream and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Pour onto graham cracker crust. Thicken thawed strawberries with cornstarch.
Cool and pour on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water together.
Pour into punch bowl. Add ginger ale and pineapple juice.
Add ice cubes or sherbet.

title: poor man's pizza
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and salt.
Cool.
Add soup, cheese and garlic salt; mix real good.

title: ham ball
directions: Blend ham, olives, pimiento and mustard.
Form into a ball. Put on serving dish; chill.
Combine cream cheese and milk.
Frost ham ball with cheese mixture.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Trim with parsley.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt and gradually add the water while stirring.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add mashed berries (add a little red food coloring, if desired).
About an hour before serving time, arrange whole berries in pie shell.
Pour strawberry glaze over top.
Chill thoroughly.
Before serving, top with sweetened whipped cream and garnish with the whole berries. (Whipped topping may be used instead of whipped cream.)

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: doris' spaghetti
directions: Brown onion and
garlic
in
fat.
Push
to side.
Sear meat, add tomato paste
plus
or
4 cans of water (to cover meat). Add salt
and
pepper.
Cook until tender.	After meat is half cooked, add American Beauty spaghetti sauce mix.
Cook spaghetti in salted
water.
Drain spaghetti.
Sauce should be fairly thick. Pour sauce over spaghetti and toss.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in butter and garlic salt.
Remove meat and add onion and green peppers and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Return meat; add tomatoes and bouillon cube.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Blend cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Add to mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat; stir occasionally 3 minutes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over cooked noodles and cover with beef mixture.

title: crunch clusters
directions: Melt chocolate pieces and peanut butter in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into 2-inch foil baking cups or onto foil or waxed paper.
Chill and store clusters in refrigerator.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, egg and salt.
Roll in balls, then brown in skillet.
In saucepan or crock-pot, combine other ingredients.
Add meatballs and simmer.

title: beef shish kabobs
directions: Cut steak into large cubes; parboil onions for about 15 minutes and cut into quarters.
Rub skewers with oil.
Spear cubes of steak, mushrooms and onions alternately on skewers.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook over barbecue grill or fire to desired doneness, placing tomatoes on end of skewers for last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and cheese until cheese is dissolved.
Mix gelatin in warm water and add to slightly cooled soup mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into well-oiled mold and chill. Unmold.
Serve with crackers.

title: bill's shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp; soak in ice water for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Mash with fork.
Mix mayonnaise, shrimp and horseradish together.
Serve with Bugles or Wheat Thins.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put brown sugar and butter in iron skillet or nonstick pan. Cook until dark brown.
Mix milk, egg yolks, flour and vanilla. Mix in a bowl and then add to brown sugar and cook until thick.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Roll out rolls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Combine cream cheese, dressing mix, mayonnaise and hot sauce and spread over cooked crust.
Sprinkle chopped veggies over cream cheese topping in layers; chill covered at least 2 hours before serving.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: baked onions with yogurt
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place the onions, unpeeled, on a foil-lined shallow pan and bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Warm a heatproof 1-quart shallow serving dish.
When onions are tender, remove from oven.
Spear the onions with a fork and peel by cutting off both ends of the onion and removing skin.
Place the onions in the warmed dish and distribute the butter and yogurt over the tops of the onions.
Sprinkle lemon juice, sugar, salt, pepper and parsley over onions and serve.
Yield:
4 onions.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake 350° for 15-20 mins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 10 minutes and drain.
Put in a square glass dish.
Cut cheese in chunks and place about in broccoli. Melt margarine and mix with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Use these as a topping for broccoli.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pour filling, pineapple and then cake mix.
Next, pour melted butter.
Top with nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Boil ham.
Wash and cut up cabbage.
Put in a big pot with enough water to cover cabbage a little bit.
Add red pepper to taste.
Add boiled ham and cook covered for 30 minutes.
When Mama made it, it was mmm...good!

title: peach almond smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Serve right then.
May have to add a little more liquid to blender.
Makes 1 to 1 1/2 cups.

title: indiana farm breakfast sausage
directions: If possible have pork at room temperature before starting.
Mix all spices together.
Mix spices with onions and pork.
Knead all ingredients into pork thoroughly.
Make patties and store in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, heat skillet and cook until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In
large
saucepan,
combine
and
heat chicken, salt, pepper, milk,
sour
cream, soup and vegetables.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with biscuits on the side or bake them right on top.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and Eagle Brand milk together. Heat in the microwave for 5 minutes. Stir well. Heat in the microwave 5 more minutes. Add vanilla. Pour into ice cream freezer then add whole milk to the fill line. Freeze as directed for ice cream freezer.

title: blueberry jelly
directions: Mix juice and water; bring to full rolling boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add Sure-Jell.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Add sugar.
Stir constantly.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix together potatoes, sour cream, soup, cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Toast 6 pieces of bread.
Tear bread into pieces and mix with melted margarine.
Put potato mixture in 8 x 12-inch Pyrex glass dish, then top with bread pieces.
Spray pan with Pam before adding potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Add bananas and dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon crumb cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add egg yolk and beat well. Add flour, spices and baking powder that have been sifted together. Mix gradually into a stiff dough. Spread with floured hand on a greased cookie sheet to about 1/2 inch thickness. Beat egg white till foamy, spread with spoon over top of dough. Press pecans into dough. Bake at 300° until light brown.

title: superbowl sunday vegetarian chili
directions: Start beans early.
It takes several hours to prepare and cook.

title: chuckwagon chili
directions: Brown beef with onion in large stew pot.

Drain off fat, then add bell pepper and spices. Mix well. Over high heat, add remaining ingredients and stir until hot and bubbly. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Serve hot. May top with grated Cheddar cheese. Serves 15.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water to cool quickly.
Drain well.

title: quick cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion and dry dressing mix.
Next mix well and refrigerate until firm.
Now roll and shape into a ball. Next roll in your chopped pecans or sunflower seeds.
Refrigerate. Serve with any snack cracker.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and mix.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. This will form its own crust while baking.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Saute together butter, bell pepper and onions.
Cook squash until done in a little water until water is cooked out.
Add cream of mushroom soup, milk, salt and black pepper; add bell pepper, onions and 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put in casserole dish and top with remaining cheese mixture.
Cover with foil and bake for 20 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lisa's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add mushroom and chicken soups, chicken broth, pimento and chicken.
Cook slowly until heated thoroughly.
Cook spaghetti until tender.
Put in large casserole dish.

title: sweet deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks; add sugar and next 4 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish, if desired.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs together and press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix together and beat for at least 15 minutes.
For top, put sliced bananas and drained pineapple. Over that, put Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, pudding, cinnamon and nuts well. Put 1/2 mixture in bottom of well-greased Bundt pan.
Put frozen rolls into greased pan.
Sprinkle the rest of the dry mix over the rolls.
Add 1/8 cup Karo syrup on top.
Slice margarine on top. Place plastic on top and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Invert on pan (bottom up).

title: two for one vegetable soup
directions: Combine the mixed vegetables, diced tomatoes, Italian tomatoes, cabbage, onions, water, corned beef hash and Cavender's seasoning.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to medium.
Cook until cabbage and onions are tender.
Add butter and Tabasco. Continue cooking for about 10 minutes.
Great served with Southern cornbread.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until thick. Cool. Add food coloring, bananas and pecans.

title: ham pepperoni roll
directions: Thaw dough overnight.
Let rise.
Divide dough in half and roll out as thin as possible.
Spread with filling.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Brush with oil.
Pinch edges together or use toothpicks to hold together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach appetizer spread
directions: In food processor, blend first 7 ingredients.
Process until smooth.
In bowl, combine with rest of the ingredients.
Blend well!
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan and bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Garnish top with fresh parsley snips and pimento. Serve warm with crackers.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt oleo; blend sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and egg.
Mix well.
Add oleo and stir well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Combine hot broth and other dry ingredients.
If not moist enough, add a little boiling water.
Dot top with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: western omelet casserole
directions: Remove crusts and butter both sides of bread.
Place 6 slices in buttered pan.
Add 1/2 of diced ham and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat: bread, ham and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender. Pour over and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes after baking before serving.
May be refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: mom's chop suey
directions: Heat butter over medium flame.
Add meat and brown well.
Add onions, celery and mushrooms; brown slightly.
Add juice drained from bean sprouts plus enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add salt and molasses.
Reduce heat to very low until meat is tender.
Add bean sprouts.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/3 cup water.
Add soy sauce.
Stir this into mixture.
Cook about 7 minutes until thickened.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple well. Mix with room temperature cream cheese, pepper and onion; add salt.

title: oriental flank steak
directions: Mix marinade ingredients well.
Pour over flank steak placed in plastic bag.
Let stand 4 to 24 hours in the refrigerator, turning often to distribute marinade.
When ready to cook, remove from marinade and place over hot coals or broil until done to your liking.
Serves 4.

title: lazy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Great sauce for barbecuing ribs.

title: saltine cracker crunch candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Let boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, coconut, crackers and vanilla.
Stir well until mixed good.
Pour into buttered pan and chill.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and cover.

title: persimmon cake(lucille ball)
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Mix together ingredients and bake in large loaf tins or 4 small ones at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marty's oven barbecue steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut steak into serving pieces.
Brown steak in oil and transfer to roasting pan.
Saute onions and add to remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over steak.
Cover and bake 2 hours.
Add extra water, if needed, to increase sauce if it is too thick after baking 1 hour.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cook oleo and flour over low heat for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Serve with chips of your choice.

title: scalloped parsley potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into wedges or slices.
Cook potatoes in a little water for about 10 minutes.
They should not get mushy.
In a saucepan, combine butter, milk and flour.
Whisk together.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and cook for about 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and potatoes.
Heat slowly.
Season to taste; sprinkle with extra parsley when serving.
Good served with grilled chicken, smoked or cooked ham or meat loaf.
Yields 4 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients; bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: skillet meal
directions: Saute pepper, celery, onion and mushrooms in fat.
Add ground beef and brown.
Pour tomatoes over this.
Spread rice over top. Cover.
Bring to boil with flame on high, then turn to simmer and cook about 25 minutes or until rice is done.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix chopped apples and sugar.
Let stand one hour; stir occasionally.
Add salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking soda and walnuts.
Mix.
Add eggs and oil; mix.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables just until tender-crisp.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place layer of vegetables.
Cover with mushrooms, water chestnuts, onion and 1/2 mushroom soup (thinned with milk).
Cover with remaining vegetables, soup and cheese. Heat in a 350° oven until bubbly (about 20 minutes).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rich, hot rolls
directions: Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour to milk mixture; beat well by hand or with electric mixer at low speed 1 minute.
Beat in eggs and yeast.
Gradually add enough remaining flour, a little at a time, to make a soft dough that leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Let stand 10 minutes before kneading.
This gives the gluten time to work so you do not need to add as much additional flour which will make the rolls tough.
Knead until smooth and satiny and no longer sticky, 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in lightly greased bowl, invert to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled; 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and turn onto board.
Shape into rolls as desired.
Cover and let rise until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown. Makes about 30 rolls, depending on size and shape.
Brush with melted butter.

If you desire a less rich roll, reduce sugar to 1/4 cup and shortening to 1/3 cup in recipe for Rich, Hot Rolls. (These rolls are often requested at our family dinners by your principal, Mrs. Shirley Lewis.

title: "preacher's" chili
directions: Cut up bacon in small pieces and brown with hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add all other ingredients.
Will probably need about 2 cups of water.
Use heavy pot to keep from scorching. Start on medium-high heat, stirring often for 15 or 20 minutes, then on low heat to simmer.
Then, hope for the best, or better yet, pray for the best!

title: favorite casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in 10-inch pan.
Add onions, green peppers, hot pepper, sugar, Accent and tomatoes and simmer slowly for 35 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas. Gradually add flour and baking soda.
Grease and flour a bread pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake for about an hour at 350°.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat; simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine in saucepan the tomatoes, onions, brown sugar, butter, bread, salt, pepper and parsley and simmer slowly for 15 minutes. Use the bread for thickening; if more is needed, use it.

title: quince cordial
directions: Cut quinces in small pieces and cover them with 4 quarts water. Add 2 pounds of sugar and boil 15 minutes or until quinces are soft.
Strain through a fine sieve or muslin bag twice.
Add 1 quart peach brandy.
"Bottle it, close, and it is fit for use."

title: italian sweet easter pie
directions: Sift the flour and salt together; cut shortening into flour. Sprinkle over egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Add water.
Mix thoroughly with a fork until blended.
Roll out and form a bottom crust in a 9-inch pie pan.
Fill unbaked crust with egg mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°.
May be served chilled or at room temperature.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir with spoon.
In another bowl, mix flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and pumpkin spice.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture, stirring with a spoon (it will be stiff).
Stir in apples and nuts.
The batter will barely cover apples.
Press into 2 loaf pans or 1 (7 x 11-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Frost, if desired (just as good without frosting).

title: date drops
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Pour into purchased pie shells.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Add milk and salt to beaten egg.
Beat well after the additions.
Add flour.
Mix.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll out to desired width of noodles you want.
Let set on board 20 minutes to dry, then cut.
Treat these noodles as you would any noodles in chicken or beef broth.

title: chicken and black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine black-eyed peas, chicken, celery, red pepper, green onions, cilantro, Italian seasoning, salt and pimento.
Add Italian dressing and mustard.
Toss well.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Toss chicken and egg until all pieces are covered.
Sprinkle 1/4 c. cornstarch over chicken, toss until all pieces are covered. Brown chicken in skillet with cooking oil.
When browned, remove from skillet.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Pound the chicken breasts between 2 sheets of waxed paper until thin.
Spread each breast with 1 tablespoon of the chilies. Put a cheese strip on top of the chilies.
Roll up each breast and tuck ends under.
Secure with a toothpick, if necessary.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine the flour and sugar.
Heat the butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Mix thoroughly. Add the buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Thin batter with marshmallows floating.
Bake in flat pan 1-inch deep at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: grandma mcquaig's pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, brown sugar, butter and vanilla together; add nuts.
Bake in oven at 375° until done.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add applesauce and mix. Add flour and mix by hand with spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil.
Cook until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in 3 1/2 cups water; remove chicken from bone. Put 1/2 stick of the butter with other ingredients in a pan with 2 1/2 cups of broth.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes.
Put chicken in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put vegetable mixture over chicken.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomatoes, pepper, rice, salt and hot sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar, oil and sugar until sugar dissolves. Pour over salad ingredients and toss until well coated. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: salami cheese balls
directions: Beat the cream cheese, olives, onion and Parmesan until smooth.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours, then shape into ball or log. Finely chop the salami.
If using a blender to do this, add small amount of water and drain off any excess liquid when chopped. Roll cheese ball in salami to cover outside.
Chill until ready to serve.
Can be frozen.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Bake crust in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Grease a casserole dish. Put in rice first and then everything else. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fish and vegetable coating
directions: Add ingredients together and mix well.
Deep fry fish after coating with mix.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Mix all ingredients in kettle.
Bake 5 hours in a 250° oven without opening the oven door.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain.
Combine potatoes, sour cream, butter, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Beat on low until light and fluffy.
Pile lightly into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour.
Toss bread crumbs in 1 tablespoon butter. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Continue baking uncovered for 30 minutes more.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Place chicken, macaroni, egg, celery and carrot in a medium bowl.
Mix well. Stir in Ranch dressing and mix well.
Makes serving for 2.

title: layered dip
directions: Spread beans onto bottom and sides of serving dish.
Top with green onion, lettuce, olives and salsa.
Serve with chips.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Set out 5 slices of bread to get hard and stale. Cut into cubes. Cream the butter.
Add the sugar to the butter.
Beat the eggs and add to sugar/butter mixture. Stir in bread.
Stir in the pineapple. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In saucepan, combine meatballs, chili sauce and jelly.
Heat thoroughly over low heat.
Serve warm.
Great party food.

title: betty's delicious chocolate candy("something for ray's sweet tooth")
directions: Mix Carnation milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes, or until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Decorate before it cools (use your artistic talent and whatever you have, walnut halves, little candy beads, big candy mints).
Cut in squares after cooling.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Liberally spray slow cooker with nonstick spray.
Trim all visible fat from steak.
Season steak with salt and pepper. Place flour in bag, add steak, shake, coating well.
Cook in slow cooker on high until tender.
Add brown gravy mix and water. Continue cooking until gravy thickens.
Serve over rice, potatoes or bread.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift, then measure flour.
Sift again with salt, sugar, soda and nutmeg.
Combine well beaten eggs, milk and melted shortening.
Turn the wet ingredients into dry ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Fold in apples last.
Drop into deep fat (375°) by spoonfuls.
Serve hot with syrup.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients (except potato chips) together in baking dish. Top with crumbled potato chips.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Mix cooked broccoli florets, soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, garlic and cheese together.
Add pepper.
Add chicken (optional). Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon puffs
directions: Boil to a syrup (about 5 minutes), 1 cup sugar, water and food coloring.
Place apples in greased shallow 8 x 12-inch pan and pour syrup over apples.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening and stir in milk.
Drop 12 spoonfuls of dough on apples and make a dent in each.
Place in dented dough a mixture of sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in hot oven at 450°.
Serve warm with cream.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery and onion; saute until partially done. Place in kettle and add the soups; mix well.
Place chow mein noodles on top.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut cream or peanut butter pie
directions: Whip milk and coconut (or peanut butter if you're making peanut butter pie).
Add pudding mix and powdered Dream Whip; blend well.
Equally divide into 3 pie shells.
Put Cool Whip on each pie.

title: danish puff
directions: 1st Mixture:
Cut oleo into 1 cup flour; add 2 tablespoons water.
Mix and spread in 2 long strips, 12 x 3-inches, on ungreased cookie sheet.
(This is easy to do by making dough into snake by rolling between hands, then patting it flat.)

title: stuffed celery sticks
directions: Clean and cut celery into 3-inch pieces (make sure celery is dry).
Mix remaining ingredients and spread onto celery pieces. Cover and refrigerate one hour.

title: peach poppy seed muffins
directions: Stir baking soda into pureed peaches.
Be prepared for the mixture to foam.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar until mixture is smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternately add flour and peach puree.
Stir in salt, vanilla and poppy seed.
Fill greased muffin cups almost to top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted into a muffin comes out clean.
Makes 12 to 18 muffins, depending on size.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with graham crackers (break squares in half at indentation) close together.
Boil together sugar, butter and margarine for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Sprinkle nuts over syrup.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and immediately transfer bars to aluminum foil with spatula.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Remove sausage from casing and break into small pieces.
Brown in small amount of olive oil. Add onion and oregano.
Drain after browning.
Add pizza sauce and stewed tomatoes.
Cook noodles until tender. Drain and rinse. Add to the meat sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place half the mixture.
Sprinkle with half the cheese and continue until all has been placed in pan. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for about 45 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter and spread in long pan evenly.
Pour graham crackers
in pan on top of butter, then pour sweetened milk on crackers
evenly, pour chocolate chips on evenly and then pour on coconut over chips.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 250° oven.

title: easy frosting
directions: Cream all together. Thin to spreading consistency with cream or milk. Spread on cooled cake.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Crumble crackers; add sugar and butter.
Mix together, then pat into pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Hand mix meal and egg.
Add buttermilk until thin consistency. Put Crisco and 1 pinch of meal in a skillet.
Cook in oven at 450° until Crisco melts and meal turns a light golden brown.
Pour 1/2 cup of melted Crisco into cornbread mixture.
Hand mix.
Pour into skillet of melted Crisco.
Cook mixture at 450° until dark golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Add egg and milk. Mix. Let batter stand 5 minutes. Drop batter by rounded tablespoon into hot oil. Cook at 375° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat eggs, Crisco, peanut butter and sugar until smooth.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder into peanut butter mixture.
Stir until all is blended well.
Stir in chocolate chips, drop by well rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, or until softly brown.

title: cream of onion soup(yield:  50 servings)
directions: Add sliced
onions
to 1 quart boiling water and simmer for 30 minutes.
Rub cooked onions through a sieve or swirl in blender to	liquify.
Combine
beef
stock,
milk,	remaining boiling water,
salt
and
pepper.	Add
to
the onions.
Melt butter or margarine in frying pan and add flour, stirring to a smooth paste. Add
to
the hot soup; mix thoroughly and bring to the
boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square or oblong pan.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix and beat eggs, milk, oil and juice.
Mix in the dry ingredients.
Take blueberries; fold into mix.
Place cake in pan; top with Streusel Topping.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally during baking.
Serve with French bread cubes or crackers.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, mustard and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir until smooth.
Add wine and crab meat.
Heat thoroughly.
Transfer to chafing dish.
Serve with Melba rounds or toast triangles.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cover chicken with water. Cook until tender.
Add ham, sausage, onion, celery and green pepper. Cook a few minutes more until vegetables are tender.
Add okra.
Add tomato sauce and chicken broth. Cook until heated through again.
Add shrimp the last 10 minutes of cooking and serve over rice.

title: simple cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Pour into graham cracker crust; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft and transparent.
Add to beans.
Mix orange juice and sugar.
Put in casserole and place orange slices on top.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven until hot. Excellent with any kind of barbecue.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (no salt).
Pick chicken off bone; set aside. Melt margarine in 1 cup chicken broth.
Stir in dressing.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put a layer of dressing, a layer of chicken and mushroom soup, diluted with 1 cup chicken broth, over all. Again add a layer of crumbs, then chicken soup, diluted with 1 cup chicken broth, over all.
Add layer of chicken.
Top with dressing and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
No salt.

title: fish stuffed with seafood
directions: Run cool water over crabmeat and shrimp and place in colander until thawed.
Drain well.
Chop and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In an uncovered medium saucepan, cook the mushrooms, onions and garlic in water until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and stir in seafood, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Finally stir in stuffing mix.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Drop 2-inches apart.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 360° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pizzelli
directions: Beat the eggs and oil.
Blend in the sugar, then the flour, a little at a time.
Mix well.

title: sister martha holland's chicken and dressing
directions: Cook hen overnight in a large crock-pot.

title: meat loaf hero sandwich(outdoor grill)
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Mix ingredients (except cheese) and pat on bottom half of bread.
Wrap in Reynolds Wrap.
Place 6 inches above coals, 30 minutes. Open Reynolds Wrap and top meat with the cheese.
Toast top half of bread and place toasted half on top of meat and serve.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Soften margarine and cream with sugar.
(Mix this pie by hand.)
Add eggs, one at a time.
(Do not beat; stir in.) Add lemon juice, grated rind, salt and cornmeal.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 30 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: emilia's spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover. Refrigerate minimum of 2 hours before serving.
Makes 3 cups.

title: keelia's baked chicken
directions: Mix together Bisquick, cheese and garlic powder.
Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Dip each piece of chicken in egg white then coat with dry mixture.
Coat 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray for easier clean up.
Bake uncovered in 400° oven for approximately 40 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: jingle bells cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Put in long casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: unbelieveable coconut pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together and bake in 2 pie pans. This forms its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: good punch
directions: Dissolve
jello in 2 quarts of boiling water.
Pour into large container.
Add
quarts
and
1 pint of water to jello mixture. Pour
in
powdered lemonade.
Mix well; add pineapple juice.
Can be served with crushed ice or frozen and mixed with 16 ounces ginger ale.

title: rita's white pizza
directions: *Olive oil (seasoned):
Keep a jar of olive oil seasoned with a lot of garlic, red pepper flakes and bay leaf.
This will give the pizza a very special flavor!

title: orange julius
directions: Add all ingredients to blender.
Crush ice before adding.
Put ice cubes in a cloth and pound with a heavy utensil on a solid surface.
After blending, pour into chilled glasses and garnish, if desired.

title: southern style potato salad
directions: Wash and boil potatoes until done.
Peel, then mash potatoes. In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients, except seasonings, eggs and cherries.
Toss, then add seasonings.
Add 2 chopped eggs; use remaining egg to place on top of potato salad (sliced). Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: butternut wafers
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; add egg yolk.
Add flour and vanilla.
Chill short time.

title: kerrie's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Pour over ribs or chicken.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add garlic, puree, chicken and salt. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stuff and roll mixture into flour tortillas. Place tortillas in Pam sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix crumbled chicken cubes, cream and cheese and pour over the tortillas.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: marinade for steak
directions: Marinate for 30 to 60 minutes.
Broil or grill.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients until fully mixed. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease 3 cake pans and divide mixture evenly into pans. Bake 25-30 minutes or until done.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat 1 1/2 cups sugar, margarine, vanilla and cream cheese on medium about 4 minutes.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Beat well.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Stir.
Add 2 tablespoons cinnamon mixture and apples to bowl.
Stir.
Spray pan.
Put in spring-form and sprinkle with remaining cinnamon mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Add onion and cook until golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat about 30 to 45 minutes.
I always double the recipe as it can easily be warmed in a microwave at a later date.

title: lemon salad
directions: Wash and drain 1 head lettuce.
Shred (do not tear) coarsely and use 1/2 to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender and set aside.
Mix butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
In another bowl prepare pudding by beating pudding mix and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold cream cheese mixture in pudding mixture and blend together.
Layer crushed cookies and pudding mixture:
1/3 cookies, 1/2 pudding, 1/3 cookies, 1/2 pudding and 1/3 cookies. Chill to set.
Poke in gummy worms and flowers.
Great for kids' birthday parties.
Serve with a plastic shovel.

title: hash-stuffed cabbage
directions: Start heating oven to 375°.
Cut cabbage into 6 wedges. Arrange in 2 or 3-quart casserole with pointed ends toward center. Pour bouillon over cabbage.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Cut sausage in chunks; fry gently.
Saute pepper in oil. Saute onion in oil.
Brown rice in oil.
Mix all ingredients. Cover with bouillon and bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Ready when rice is cooked.
Sprinkle chopped almonds on top.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Do not beat. Flour and grease tube pan/Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom souffle
directions: In the melted butter, saute mushrooms, onions, celery, green peppers, parsley and garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put half the bread in bottom of pan (separate pan).
Add mayonnaise to sauteed mixture.
Pour mixture over bread in pan.
Add the remaining bread.
Mix eggs, milk and soup together and pour over bread.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
After rice is done, add margarine and cheese to hot rice and stir until blended.
Add remaining ingredients to rice mixture and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hot cheese potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cube 3/4 x 3/4-inch.
Fry bacon; chop and drain.
Put all ingredients in a roasting pan and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Serves 20 people.

title: microwave chocolate banana pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and butter 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir every 30 seconds.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Spread evenly in crust.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or until firm.
Arrange banana slices over chocolate.
Mix pudding and pie mix according to directions on package with a whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas in crust.
Spread Cool Whip over pie. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Cook on stove until thick and eat with biscuits.

title: pot roast
directions: Put enough water to cover roast or better yet, a mixture of half water and half beef stock.
Wipe the meat well with a cloth or paper towel.
Mix the flour, salt and pepper and rub into the roast.
Have a Dutch oven on the coals or in the oven at 350° with the interior of pot oiled.
Sear the roast well on all sides.
Add the solid ingredients and pour in the liquid.
Cover the Dutch oven and bury in coals or cook in oven at 350°.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
No pot watching is needed.
If cooked in the ground, coals should be renewed at midnight in cooking.
Serves 6.

title: munchies
directions: Mix first four ingredients together; pour over the oyster crackers.
Mix well. (May place in brown bag and shake to mix.) Store in airtight containers. Shake well each time before serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in narrow strips.
Stir-fry until brown.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cover with beef stock and simmer covered 10 minutes. Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to mixture and cook 10 minutes stirring until thick.
May be served with rice.

title: fancy corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old-fashioned chicken noodle soup
directions: In a 4-quart casserole, combine the chicken, carrots, mushrooms, zucchini, red pepper, water, white wine, lemon juice, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on High power for 10 minutes.
Add the noodles, a handful at a time, so they don't stick together.
Stir.
Cover and return to microwave for 6 minutes on High power.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lazy u cake
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa and water; bring to rapid boil in saucepan.
Pour over flour mixture and stir well.
Do not use mixer!
Add buttermilk (1 tablespoon lemon juice in 1 cup milk can substitute for buttermilk; let stand for 5 minutes), eggs (slightly beaten), soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Coarsely shred the carrots using a food processor or mandolene.
Toss carrots in a mixing bowl with remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: crab meat and vegetable salad
directions: In a medium-size saucepan, cook rice according to directions; let cool.
In a large bowl, combine rice, crab meat, peas, carrots and scallions; mix well.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice, pepper and garlic powder; stir.
Stir this into rice mixture, tossing to coat.
Chill salad.
On a platter, arrange bed of lettuce and top with salad.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg, mix well, then oil and mix well.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well and form into balls the size of small walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake for about 12 minutes.
Allow to cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing.
If desired, sprinkle warm cookies with granulated sugar for extra sweetness! These really are "the world's best" cookie!
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add mushrooms and Lawry's mix (with water).
Pour 1 can tomato sauce in bottom of baking dish. Add a few teaspoons hot sauce.
Roll a little hamburger mixture and shredded cheese (and black olives, if desired) in each shell. Roll up shell and place in baking dish.
Pour the other cans of sauce over them and sprinkle remaining hamburger and cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts (approximately 20 minutes).

title: diabetic strawberry pie
directions: Combine the jello, pudding and water in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the combination comes to a good boil. Take off stove and let cool completely.

When cool, add the diced strawberries (with the Equal already stirred up in the sliced strawberries) to the jello pudding mixture and either pour in a regular baked crust or in a graham cracker crust.

title: caramel banana pie
directions: Cover can of Eagle Brand milk with water and boil for 3 hours. Keep refrigerated until needed.
Slice bananas into baked pie crust.
Spoon Eagle Brand milk over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, mixing well after each addition.

title: tuna dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Mix in eggs and tuna.
Add pepper.
Stir well.
Chill and serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Cook chicken in soy sauce and oil until done.
Add rest of ingredients and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Stir soup and milk to make a creamy consistency.
Add rest of ingredients, except eggs.
Fold in eggs carefully.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Store, covered, in refrigerator at least 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, uncovered. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix creamed mixture and dry ingredients; chill and roll into small
balls.
Mash
down
on a cookie sheet covered with foil with
a
glass
dipped into granulated sugar; press down. Bake at 325° until light brown around edges.

title: molasses oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening, molasses and sugar.
Stir in flour which has been mixed with oats, spices, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Seedless raisins may be added, if desired.
Yields 9 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Microwave for 30 seconds; cool. Combine broccoli, seeds, raisins and bacon.
Mix dressing and broccoli mixture together.
Chill and serve.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan in oven.
Remove from oven when melted. Mix flour, sugar, milk and vanilla together, then pour into melted margarine.
Drop by spoonfuls sweetened peaches into batter (do not stir).
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Put sugar, cream, butter and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly and bring to a rolling boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.

title: crunchy pound cake
directions: Let eggs reach room temperature.
Sift flour.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add 1/2 of flour, mixing well. Add the other 1/2 of flour, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Mix well.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Top will crack and will be crunchy.
May be iced or glazed.

title: basic tomato sauce
directions: Boil juice or tomatoes down until thick.
Add all other ingredients and cook until thick again.
Take up and seal in jars. Great for spaghetti, chili or lasagna sauce.

title: jambalaya salad
directions: Combine and serve on salad greens.

title: evelyn's spaghetti
directions: Fry bacon until almost crisp, drain off about half the fat. Add chopped onions and brown along with bacon. Add 2 large cans of stewed tomatoes and heat to boil. Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: dressing
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion.
Mix all together and leave until soft.
Mix again well and bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Leave uncovered.

title: breakfast bars
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together,
add all liquids.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pans (greased and floured).
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add remaining ingredients. Pour into either two bread pans or one Bundt pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: heath bar candy cake
directions: Bake devil's food cake as directed on box.
Remove from oven and allow to cool.
Poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon. Pour condensed milk over cake and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crushed Heath bars over this.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain juice off corn; put in bowl.
Add egg and flour.
Fry in skillet in Crisco.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: excellent prune cake
directions: Cook and chop the prunes before measuring.
Cream the butter, sugar and spices until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after addition of each.
Sift flour, measure and sift again with baking powder, soda and salt. Add dry ingredients alternately with prune juice and milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in prunes and walnuts.
Pour into two greased and floured 8-inch layer cake pans (lined with paper, if desired).
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Remove from pan and cool on rack. Serve plain or frosted or serve warm with a tart lemon or orange sauce.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, soup, sugar, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cool.
Drain carrots.
Pour dressing over carrots, onions and peppers; cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: orange black walnut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except walnuts) with wire whisk. Mix well, then add walnuts. Pour into 1 unbaked deep-dish pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm. Let cool before slicing.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook all together (except brandy) for 1 hour, then add brandy. Best if let set in refrigerator a few days.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix well together and add 1 cup milk.
Beat the egg whites of your 2 eggs; fold into the other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
(If top browns too fast, turn down to 250° for it must get to a custard in center.)

title: butter banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Put in 9-inch bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: real red devil's food cake
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well. Cook for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Toss lightly and chill until serving time.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil coffee in 5 cups water; add sugar.
Stir to dissolve. Cool.
Add grain alcohol or vodka and rest of water.
Add vanilla. Pour into empty milk jug or gallon container.
Shake.

title: california frijole salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil and salt.
Combine beans in large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over bean mixture; toss to mix well.
Cover.
Chill for several hours.
Toss again and drain before serving.

title: bourbon balls
directions: In a medium sized mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together the bourbon and corn syrup.
Add wafer crumbs, pecans and 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Mix thoroughly until soft and sticky.
Spoon portions (1/2 tablespoon each) of mixture onto waxed paper generously covered with confectioners sugar.
Roll each portion into a small ball; roll again in confectioners sugar.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight before serving.
Balls will keep for weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 36.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: In double boiler, mix
milk
with cheese cut into small pieces.
Heat until smooth.
Add vinegar and dry mustard.
Set aside to cool.
Cut pimentos
into small pieces; add to cheese mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: cabbage and tomato
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving grease.
Crumble bacon, set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to grease; cook over medium heat uncovered for 15 minutes.
Stir in bacon and serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; set aside.
Cook garlic, celery and onion until transparent.
Stir in flour, soup, cheese and milk; cook until bubbly.
Stir in tuna, peas and noodles carefully.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients together, then mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar with the first five ingredients.
Let stay in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water until dissolved.
Stir in marshmallows until almost dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: crock-style beans
directions: In saucepan, bring water and beans to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl; cover and chill.
Drain beans; reserve 1 cup liquid. Transfer beans and reserved liquid into crock-pot.
Stir in pork, onion, molasses, brown sugar and mustard.
Cover; cook on low heat for 12 to 14 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cream dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, yogurt, sugar and vanilla in blender until smooth.
Blend in peanuts until chopped.
Put in serving dish and garnish with peanuts.
Serve chilled with wedges of Granny Smith apples.

title: chicken and green bean dinner
directions: You will need one oven cooking bag.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, heat enough oil to cover bottom of skillet, one or two tablespoons of sesame oil will enhance the flavor.
Add green onions, celery, green pepper and chicken.
Stir well and saute for about 1 minute.
Add rice, stirring quickly so it won't stick.
Add soy sauce; mix well.
Push mixture to one side and drain oil to empty side.
Scramble eggs in open area. When set, stir into rice mixture.
Serve immediately.
Additional soy sauce may be sprinkled on top of individual servings.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions. Use 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is still hot, poke holes in it. Mix the can of cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk together. Pour over hot cake. Let cool completely. Top with carton of Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut over top. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving (the longer the better). Store in refrigerator.

title: upside-down delight
directions: Brown bacon and crumble in a 10 or 12-inch frying pan. Arrange pepper rings and sliced olives in pan.
Cover pepper and olives with crumbled bacon, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook and simmer meat; saute onions and garlic, stir in tomato soup and chili powder.
Spoon meat mixture over corn, pepper and olive rings.

title: maree's hot milk cake
directions: Melt butter in milk in saucepan.
Beat eggs until frothy (3 minutes).
Add sugar and while beating add flour.
Add milk mixture; add 2 teaspoons baking powder and 2 teaspoons vanilla. Beat until mixed.
Bake at 350° in 9-inch pans 20 to 25 minutes or in tube pan for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: grilled kabobs with rice
directions: Place on skewer.
Grill until beef is browned on outside, but not done.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Beat Cool Whip, condensed milk, lemon juice and pineapple. Fold in nuts and pour into baked pie crusts.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: scripture bars
directions: Beat Jeremiah 17:11 until light.
Add Jeremiah 6:20 and Psalms 55:21; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add all chopped ingredients and flavoring; mix well.
Bake in a shallow cake pan. Cut into bars and roll in Jeremiah 6:20.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Crumble Blue cheese.
Mix with other ingredients.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: fairy fluff
directions: Whip cream stiff.
Add ground peanut brittle, marshmallows and drained pineapple.
Mix well and set in refrigerator to cool. Serve on sliced angel food cake or in cream puff shells.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spray a 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange chicken, bone side down, in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine soup and water; spoon over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until done.
Serve with pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry jello whip
directions: Put pineapple plus juice and jello in saucepan and let come to a boil, remove and put in large mixing bowl.
Let cool.
When cool, in mixing bowl take jello mixture and fluff or turn cottage cheese and Cool Whip until well mixed.
Put in a pretty bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: tomato basil cream pasta sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Add tomato paste and basil.
Slowly stir in whipping cream.
Keep fire at medium temperature.
Do not allow to boil.
Serve over any pasta dish.

title: horseradish and beets(hren)
directions: Cook beets until a fork will go through them with a little help.
Remove and grate.
Add all the rest of the ingredients. Season.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pizza bread sticks
directions: Place pizza shell on cookie sheet.
Spread enough oil over dough to cover.
Sprinkle well with cheese and garlic salt.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cut into strips immediately.
Serve with warmed spaghetti sauce.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a blender.
Cover.
Add ice cubes, one at a time, blending in between until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cut the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put remaining ingredients in blender.
Whip together.
Pour over base.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat. Bake in tube pan about 1 hour at 350°. While hot, sprinkle with 1/4 cup powdered sugar and remaining grated chocolate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper. Stir in vegetables and chicken. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until it bubbles.
While casserole cooks, cut biscuits into quarters.
Remove dish from oven, stir and place biscuits over mixture.
Bake 15 more minutes or until biscuits are golden.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, salad oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt. Let stand while preparing remaining ingredients.
Toss all ingredients together and serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough in slices 1/8-inch thick.
Line a greased 14-inch pizza pan with slices overlapping.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes, cool.

title: hamburger and mushroom gravy
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Form ground beef into patties and place in skillet.
Fry until brown and cooked through.
While meat is cooking, put onion on top and salt and pepper.
After meat is thoroughly cooked, pour in soup and milk. Cover and simmer on low heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: jamaican christmas pudding
directions: Wash fruits if necessary.
Drain and in a jar or bottle, add wine, rum, brandy, stout and burnt sugar and mix well.
Seal tightly and place in a cool area for about 4 weeks.

title: great stickies
directions: Roll out dough as for pie crust.
Pour melted butter over crust.
Pour and pat brown sugar over butter.
Top with raisins and nuts.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Slice with a sharp knife.
Bake in a 325° oven until done, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the other five ingredients until smooth.
(Batter will be thin.) Pour on top of butter, then spoon pie filling on top of batter.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
(Other fruit filling can be used if desired.) Serve with your favorite vanilla sauce.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Mix uncooked peas and peanuts; add celery and onion.
Mix salad dressing, sour cream, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce together and blend into pea and peanut mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature a few minutes before serving.

title: instant cappucino
directions: Mix and store in an air-tight container.

title: sister mable's caramel corn
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring over medium-high heat.
