Stirring constantly, boil rapidly about 5 minutes until mixture reaches 260° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda quickly, but thoroughly.
Pour at once over popped corn in a large roasting pan.
Stir gently until all kernels are coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Turn out at once onto wax paper.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: blueberry-cheese cake(simple to make)
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool. In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy; fold in the whipped cream. Spread over each cake. Top with pie filling. Chill 4 hours or overnight. Yield: 24 to 30 servings.

title: blackberry bars
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour with white sugar and butter.
Blend to fine crumbs and press in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then mix raisins, jam and 1 tablespoon flour and pour over baked crust.

title: southwestern chicken-corn chowder
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat; add chicken, onion, garlic, and saute 10 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups half-and-half and next 6 ingredients; cook over low heat, stirring often, 15-20 minutes.
Stir in 2 tablespoons cilantro. Serve immediately.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: mock chicken fried steak
directions: Combine egg, 1/2 cracker crumbs, milk, onion, chili powder, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add meat; mix well.
Shape into 6 (1/2-inch thick) patties and coat with remaining cracker crumbs. Cook in hot oil over medium heat until done.

title: white sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir over heat until thick.
White sauce can be used for many recipes, but it is especially good served over the salmon loaf.

title: chicken rice-a-roni
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut up in pieces.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Saute with butter.
Cut up onions and mushrooms; cook until almost done.
Mix all with Rice-A-Roni. When ready to serve, add sour cream.

title: frozen strawberry fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix all other ingredients and add to cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in 9 ounces of whipped topping.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish; cover and freeze.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine, Worcestershire, garlic powder and celery salt and pour over other ingredients.
Heat oven to 250°.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box, adding a package of Dream Whip to cake mix. Bake cake according to package directions. ln mixing bowl, combine condensed milk and pina colada mix. After removing cake from oven, punch holes in cake while it is still hot. Pour the condensed milk and pina colada mix over the hot cake. Refrigerate cake until cool. Spread Cool Whip on top of cooled cake and top with coconut.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together; beat in sugar.
Fold in flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs; fold into mixture.
Turn into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Do not overcook.
Top each slice with ice cream while still warm. May be reheated.
Serves 6.
Yum.
This makes for a quick dessert if in a hurry.

title: refrigerator fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in micro-safe bowl in microwave.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off wax paper.
Cut as desired.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half. Scoop pulp into a bowl; mash with a potato masher or fork just until slightly chunky. Stir in sour cream and next 5 ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy pan.
Put on stove; stir until clear.
Cook to 225° or just before soft ball stage. Put 1/3 cup into egg whites, slowly.
Cook remainder until soft ball stage.
Pour 1/3 into egg whites.
Put remainder on stove and cook until soft crack stage.
Add quickly to egg whites and beat until it begins to lose its shine.
Add nuts and vanilla flavoring.
Spoon onto wax paper and let set until firm.

title: flo's chocolate sauce
directions: Mix ingredients; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over cake, ice cream, etc.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat together.
Place in 1 gallon can from electric ice cream freezer.
Fill can with whole milk; turn on following instructions with freezer.

title: springtime slaw
directions: Combine carrots, cabbage, pineapple and walnuts in a large bowl.
Toss with yogurt until well coated.
Chill and serve. Makes 5 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and chopped pecans.
Press into bottom of a buttered sheet cake pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and set aside for 20 minutes. Mix the next 6 ingredients together.
Add oatmeal.
Sift together last three ingredients and add to oatmeal mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
When slightly cool, frost.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes. Cut in half lengthwise. Scoop out the inside. Combine insides with cream cheese and chopped onion. Fill potato skins with mixture. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bacon bits. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: scallops in orange sauce
directions: Fry scallops in margarine in very hot skillet until very brown.
Turn.
Pour sauce made from balance of ingredients over scallops and continue to fry about 2 more minutes to finish cooking.
Drizzle sauce over scallops to serve.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl, then pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture boils. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes or bowl. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg; serve warm or cold.

title: barley pilaf casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onions, mushrooms and barley. Cook on medium heat until highly browned.
Place in casserole dish.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Rinse nuts with hot water.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Coarsely chop nuts; set aside.
Press coconut into bottom and up sides of pastry shell; set aside.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients; stir in nuts.
Pour filling into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake an additional 35 minutes or until set.
Fold cream of coconut into whipped cream; serve whipped cream mixture with pie. Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: layered salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package; cool.
Place 1 1/2 cups of lettuce in 2-quart straight-sided bowl.
Add half the onions with half the rice.
Add a layer of peas.
Repeat lettuce, onion and rice layers.
Top with kidney beans and add remaining lettuce. Chill.
Prepare salad dressing mix as directed on package.
About 1 hour before serving, pour evenly over salad and chill.
(Be creative with salad dressing mix.
Use a flavored vinegar, such as red wine or tarragon.
Try a specialty oil, such as olive or sesame.)

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in 2 cups boiling water.
Boil 7 to 9 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in milk and cheese gradually, stirring well after each addition.
Add salt and pepper; mix well.
Cook over low heat until sauce thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour macaroni into sauce, stirring to cool.
Pour into lightly greased 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Can also be topped with buttered bread crumbs.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Sift all-purpose flour with baking powder, soda and salt. Stir in graham flour and walnuts.
Beat egg lightly; beat in brown sugar, molasses, buttermilk and shortening.
Stir into dry mixture, just until all of the flour is moistened.
Spoon into 3 greased 1-pound size cans or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Turn out onto wire racks.
Serve warm or cold.

title: rosettes
directions: Beat eggs slightly with sugar and salt; add flour and milk. Beat until smooth.
Set aside to set.
This is a must, as it prevents bubbles remaining on top of batter.
Using a deep frypan, heat oil to 320°.
Place rosette iron in the oil to be heated. When oil reaches 320° remove iron, tapping it lightly against the edge of pan.
Dip hot iron into batter, being careful not to spill batter over top edge of iron.
Immerse rosette in hot oil for at least 20 seconds to obtain light brown color.

title: national clarion squash
directions: In 2 tablespoons of olive
oil, saute peppers, onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Remove from	pan,
then
saute
squash 5 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and
add	a liberal amount of butter for extra flavor.

title: salmonettes
directions: Drain salmon.
Reserve 1/4 cup of liquid.
Mix salmon, egg and onion.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to liquid and stir into salmon mixture.
Drop from spoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown (approximately 7 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in salt and oil. Gradually add flour and sugar.
Beat until smooth, then turn out on lightly floured board and knead until dough is elastic.
Place dough in a deep bowl; brush top with oil and cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in size.
Divide; roll each into ball. Press with fingers on pizza pan.
Top with topping and bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: beef ragout
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Stir well; bake about 3 hours at 325°.
Very good served over brown rice.
(For a crisp taste, a small can of water chestnuts may be added; very good without them, however.)

title: cheese dip
directions: Cream cheese until smooth.
Chop meat and onions fine; form into ball.
Chill overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: squash-carrot casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion, uncovered, in boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Drain well.
(For winter squash, cut into large pieces, remove seeds and steam 10 to 15 minutes; peel and slice.)
Saute onion.
Combine stuffing mix with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the stuffing mixture in a 12-inch quiche dish or 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture atop.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing around edge of dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for quiche dish and 30 to 35 minutes for baking dish.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage-beef casserole
directions: Cook sausage, beef, onion and pepper together; drain well. Add mushrooms and the package of uncooked brown wild seasoned rice or any long grain wild rice with seasonings.
Also, add soups and water; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with cheese for last 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ingredients together, crushing tortilla chips on top. Serve with sour cream and Catalina dressing.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Combine with other ingredients (except chicken) and mix well.
Place each breast skin side up.
Trim all excess fat.
Loosen skin from one side and stuff with 1/3 cup of filling under skin.
Tuck the skin and meat under the breast.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Make a well in center.
Add liquid mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients. Pour into 3 well-greased pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: Take love and loyalty; mix it thoroughly with faith.
Blend it with tenderness, kindness and understanding.
Add friendship and hope, sprinkle abundantly with laughter.
Bake it with sunshine. Serve daily with generous helpings.
(This recipe was given to me by Bob's grandparents.
It must work.
They celebrate their 68th anniversary this year.)

title: huckleberry cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Mix flour and baking powder in. Add milk.
Mix all together.
Fold in berries.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake in an 8-inch square pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: one bowl pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 30 minutes.
Pour batter into a large size tube pan that has been greased with butter or oleo and coated with granulated sugar.
This makes a sweet crust on cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Batter will be thin.

title: viva la chicken tortilla
directions: Wrap chicken in foil and bake 1 1/2 hours. Bone and cut into chunks; save the juice. Cut tortillas in 1 inch squares or triangles. Mix soup, onion, salsa and milk.

title: rice casserole
directions: Note:
May substitute 2 beef bouillon cubes and 2 cups water for beef consomme and 1/2 cup water.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients. While hot, fold in the ice cream. Refrigerate overnight. Excellent in Tupperware Jell-O mold, or put in a salad mold or in a pretty bowl.

title: edwards' breakfast casserole(combines eggs and smoked country sausage links!)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice sausages in 1/8-inch thick circles or coins; saute in an ungreased frying pan for 2 to 4 minutes.
Drain well.
Trim crusts from bread and fit into bottom of dish.
Distribute sausage over bread.
Place eggs, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and milk in blender and blend well.
Spread cheeses over sausage and cover with milk mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and allow to sit in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: sour pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers. Place in pint jars. Pour cold water over them; seal. Put in refrigerator overnight. Next morning, drain water off. Bring to a boil all ingredients; pour over slices. Seal again. Ready to eat in 3 weeks.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In pot, cook meat and onion until brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 3 hours or until thick.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Add milk and oleo.
Bring to rolling boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, chopped nuts and quick oats.
Let peanut butter melt prior to adding oats.
Mix and spoon onto wax paper. Cool until set.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed and cool to warm.
Add chocolate cake mix and mix well.
Put on a cookie sheet (one with sides).
Put chocolate chips and chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: june's bean dish
directions: Mix together and pour over 2 or 3 cans of string beans.
Put in oven and get hot through.
Then I add grated cheese on top and put back into oven to melt.
Real good.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut in half lengthwise and remove seeds. Lightly mix beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Pile into pepper halves.
Arrange in shallow baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in cream.
Add sugar, butter, beaten eggs, salt and flavorings.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Add a little of chopped raisins and dates.
Bake about 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fettuccini a la lolly
directions: Lightly saut garlic, scallions and tomato.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add wine and reduce slightly.
Add cream, chicken and 1/2 cup shredded parmesan.
Simmer 5 minutes or so, adjust seasonings, and serve over cooked noodles.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: smoked shrimp agean
directions: Shell and devein raw shrimp.
Wash.
Marinate shrimp overnight in remaining ingredients.
Skewer shrimp shoulder to shoulder. Build a medium fire.
Place damp hickory chips on white coals. Cook shrimp for 4 minutes.
(Cover to grill should be closed.) Brush with marinade.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Turn shrimp.
Brush with marinade.
Add more hickory chips.
Smoke 10 minutes more. (Shrimp should not be placed directly over the coals.)

title: spice raisin cupcakes
directions: Put raisins and water in saucepan, bring to boil for 10 minutes.
Add lard and salt, let cool.
In separate bowl, mix rest of ingredients.
Add to first mixture when cooled.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
18 cupcakes.

title: crab spread
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients. Add garlic salt to taste.
Spread on pizza pan in the shape of a "pizza crust."
Top with chili sauce, then crab, then parsley.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let set in refrigerator overnight. Serve with crackers.
Looks like a pizza, very pretty.

title: sand and gravel
directions: Rub margarine into flour.
Line pan with this mixture and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix
remaining ingredients well together before spreading on flour/margarine.
Bake 25 minutes in slow oven (300°).
Cut in squares.

title: sweet and sour spare ribs(frypan dinner)
directions: Cut ribs to bite size. Put flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag. Shake to blend. Add spare ribs, a few at a time, and shake to coat with flour mixture. Heat large frying pan; add butter the size of an egg; wait until surface of pan is covered with melted butter. Then add ribs;
frying pan temperature should

be 325° to 350°. Brown ribs; turn and brown other side. Meanwhile in medium saucepan combine hot water from tap, brown sugar, tomato catsup, and vinegar drained from pickles. Heat until almost boiling. Dissolve cornstarch in cold water and add to saucepan; stir until thickened. Add sauce mixture to ribs in frying pan; stir occasionally; put top on pan and simmer - the longer the better - stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Serve with rice and steamed vegetables, (green beans, carrots, broccoli or corn make colorful choices).

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool. Frost with icing.

title: "brigadorious"(brazilian recipe)
directions: Put ingredients in saucepan.
Over medium heat, stir until it becomes thick and rolls from the bottom and sides of pan, keeping it stirred to avoid sticking to the pan.
When it comes from sides and bottom of pan, turn out on a well buttered pan to cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at
until
knife blade comes out clean when inserted in center of pie.

title: danish cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together, then mix into batter with a mixing spoon.
Then add diced apples and nuts. Batter is stiff!
Press into greased, floured pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: "ritzy" bibbed bits
directions: Melt chocolate and paraffin over low heat.
Dip and coat crackers, using a long 2-tined fork.
Cool on wax paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until brown around the edges.
Good served with crackers or vegetables.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas and pimentos.
Grate cheese into peas and pimentos (I use about 4 to 6 ounces).
Sprinkle with sugar, around 1/8 cup. Spoon in enough Miracle Whip to hold together.
Mix well.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Add egg, ginger, salt and soda.
Add sifted flour.
Roll a small amount (size of marble).
Dip in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet (may flatten with spoon).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Preheat oven.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Simmer bouillon in water until dissolved. Add onions and celery. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Add carrots and potatoes. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Add broccoli.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Add soup and cheese.
Simmer until well blended and cheese is melted.

title: roger's heartburn city chili
directions: Add beans, onion, picante sauce, tomatoes and Tabasco in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Brown ground round.
Drain well.
Add chili powder to beef.
Add beef to crock-pot and cook 1 hour.
Reduce heat to low and cook 1 hour.
Serve with sour cream, cheese and Rolaid's.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: diet bran muffins(copied from "guild book," 1941)
directions: Beat egg; add molasses.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Lastly, add bran and beat.
Bake in greased muffin pans in hot oven (375°) for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple in large saucepan; heat on stove until jello dissolves.
Do not boil.
Let cool; mix buttermilk and cool whip until well mixed.
Add to jello mixture. Pour into 8 by 12 inch oblong dish, and sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine cheeses.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 2 logs or balls or 1 large if preferred.
(If placed in the refrigerator for a few minutes, easier to shape.)
Roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Remove from heat and drain off grease. Do not wipe skillet clean, but allow a few tablespoons of grease in pan.
Put a few drops of lemon juice in skillet and add beans and crumbled bacon.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix the butter, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Stir in the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Chill about 1 hour.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls into the sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned but still soft.

title: wild plum muffins
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and baby food. Stir just until mixed.
Spray mini muffin pans with Pam.
Fill pans with batter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 dozen muffins.

title: "poppin' fresh" sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat pudding and milk together.
Add nutmeg and cinnamon.
Fold in sour cream.
Add chilled raisins; save a few for the top.
Pour into baked crust and top with whipped cream and raisins.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: In large cooker, combine the first 9 ingredients.
Cook 2 hours.
Add tomato paste.
Cook 2 more hours.
Can and seal.

title: caramelitas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl and blend until crumbly. Reserve half.
Press remaining half of crumb mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans on top of crust.
Stir flour into caramel topping and drizzle over chocolate chips and pecans.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture and bake 15 minutes.
Cool 1 to 2 hours before cutting.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: hot pineapple
directions: Combine the pineapple, sugar, flour and Cheddar cheese; mix well.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Mix the crushed crackers with the melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tangy meat loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Set aside. Mix rest. Add 1/2 of sauce. Shape into loaf. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. (Drain grease. Top with rest of sauce 15 minutes before done.)

title: citrus nut bread
directions: In bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda. Combine egg, orange juice, lemon juice and cooking oil.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until the dry ingredients are moist.
Fold nuts into batter.
Pour batter into 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap in foil and store overnight before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: quick whole wheat bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, egg, molasses, oil, baking soda and salt.
Add flour and buttermilk, mixing thoroughly.
Spoon mixture into greased and lightly floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: depression cake
directions: In medium saucepan, put the raisins. Add the boiling water. Boil raisins until only 1 cup of liquid is left.
Let stand until cool.
Cream the shortening with sugar, then add liquid from raisins.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together. Add to creamed mixture.
When well blended, add raisins, nuts and gumdrops. Bake in moderate oven (approximately 375°).

title: fruited iced tea
directions: Let teabags steep in boiling water.
Remove and add sugar. Add frozen juices and enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: dumplings for two
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
This will make a dough.
Roll dough very thin and cut into strips.
Drop in boiling broth.
Turn heat down and cook 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup sweet milk and a dash of black pepper (to suit your taste).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add nutmeg, salt and eggs, one at a time; then add cream.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly and drop or roll out and cut.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: one, two, three
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients together.
Form small balls by rolling in palms of hand.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Then again with soda and salt. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and cream together well. Add vanilla and make into balls and flatten with fork after placing in cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350°.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in oven in a large thin casserole dish or small cake pan.
Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Mix in 2/3 cup of peach juice.
Pour this mixture over the melted oleo.
Put peaches in on top of this.
Bake at 350° until it gets brown around edges.

title: cavatina
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Cook meat mixture until browned; drain grease.
Add Ragu; heat until warm. In a long pan, layer lasagne noodles and other noodles.
Add meat sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: whole wheat sopaipillas
directions: Mix
dry ingredients; add oil and water.
Knead to make a soft
dough.
Let stand a few minutes.
Roll about 1/8-inch thick. Cut into squares.
Fry in oil (hot).
Drain.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onion, salt and pepper in just enough water to cover until potatoes are tender.
Add additional water if the mixture is not
"soupy" enough.
Add flour mixed well into milk. Bring mixture to boil again and serve.
Garnish with chives, green onions, cilantro or parsley.

title: chili
directions: Fry ground beef, onions, garlic and season to taste.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and beans.
Simmer.

title: little ham sandwiches
directions: Blend together butter, mustard, sauce, poppy seed and onion until smooth.
Cut rolls in two.
Place spread on both sides.
Add ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: cherry crumb pie
directions: Make cream cheese mixture (softened) to which sugar has been added.
Spread over the cooled crumb layer.
The second layer is a whipped envelope of whip mix.
For the last layer, spoon ready mixed cherry pie filling over all.
Allow to set several hours or overnight.

title: brambles
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and raisins.
After pie crust is put in muffin tins, fill with 1 tablespoon of creamed mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: john wayne casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Drain peppers, remove seeds and dice them.
In large bowl combine grated cheese and green chilies, turn into well buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch (2-quart) casserole dish.
Beat egg whites in large bowl until stiff peaks form.
Beat egg yolks in separate bowl with milk, flour, salt and pepper; mix well until blended.
"Gently" fold egg whites into egg yolk mixture.
Do not beat!
Pour egg mixture over the cheese mixture in the casserole, using a fork, kind of ooze it through the cheese.
Don't whip it up.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large boiler, empty mix.
Add paste, rinsing each can with 1/2 can water.
Add undrained tomatoes (mash before adding). Add basil, oregano, onion and garlic.
Stir well.
Stir in 3 pints of water and sugar.
Bring to a boil; simmer 2 hours.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and sugar; set aside.
Combine egg yolks, buttermilk and butter; add to flour mixture, stirring briskly until blended.

title: norwegian coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in margarine.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Blend liquid ingredients and gently mix with dry ingredients, only until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Spread in a greased and floured 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle remaining cup of crumbs over batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: "mouth watering" baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine sour cream with spices, juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Coat each piece of chicken in mixture and let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight or all day.

title: biscuit mix
directions: The day you want to use, add milk.
Roll out with flour.
I use milk with a little vinegar.

title: dream cake
directions: Make cake in 2 (8-inch) round pans.
In separate bowl, mix chocolate and vanilla puddings together with 4 cups milk; let set. Layer in large round glass trifle bowl: cake, pudding, Cool Whip, 3 crushed toffee bars.
Repeat.
Best if made 24 hours before and refrigerated.

title: pizza
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water in a bowl.
Set aside until foamy.
Place 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in center.
Pour yeast mixture and 2 tablespoons olive oil in well and mix to form a dough ball.
Let dough rest for 5 minutes.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface (cookie sheet or pizza pan) with floured fingers.
Make sure dough is smooth and elastic, knead and add additional flour, if necessary.

title: peanutty pear slaw
directions: Combine
first	5
ingredients in medium bowl.	Stir in sour cream.
Mix
well.	Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: kraut slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and flour alternately to mixture.
Add vanilla and fold in egg whites and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost cake with white icing and decorate with halves or hickory nuts.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Let cool and tear into small pieces or cubes.
Place chicken in bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with broccoli.
Mix other ingredients together except herb dressing and butter and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle on dressing.
Drizzle melted butter over dressing.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or a little bit longer.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 355° Combine first five ingredients in large bowl, blend well. Add pecans. Pour into crust. Bake 50 to 55 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Slice all 1/4-inch thick and cube.
Mix all above ingredients and sprinkle with "fancy" shredded Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese. Can blend in Italian salad dressing or leave without.
There is enough flavor to eat plain.
Or you can use your favorite dressing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine using hands cheese, cream cheese and margarine.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Make into ball and garnish with nuts.

title: nicole's vegetable and chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix broth and cornstarch; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine chicken strips, soy sauce and 1 teaspoon salt.
Heat one tablespoon oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken mixture.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until done.
Remove chicken from skillet to serving dish.

title: savory lamb chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides. Mix all other ingredients well and pour over chops. Cover tightly and simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Turn once during cooking. Add more water if necessary to prevent burning (as little as possible).
There shouldn't be any liquid left when you serve them.
Serve hot.
Garlic powder can be substituted for the garlic salt, if desired.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare and slice the eggplant and onions.
Slice the pepper. Brown in frying pan in oil.
Place the browned vegetables in a greased casserole, alternating with the sliced tomatoes.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Coat a large baking dish with cooking spray. Layer half each of potatoes, onions and tomatoes in dish; sprinkle with half each of salt, thyme and rosemary. Repeat layers and drizzle with olive oil. Cover and bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: crab or shrimp ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Chill well. Cover with cocktail
sauce
(catsup and horseradish) and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender and drain well.
Mash well with 1/2 stick butter.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add 2 well-beaten eggs and sour cream.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes. Add crumbled cracker crumbs on top; return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: lynn's potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Slice onion and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with butter and bake until butter melts.
Fold in potatoes until well coated with butter.
Add sausage and 1/2 of cheese. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is "gooey".

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg is added. Blend in all of the flour.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Using the highest speed on the mixer, beat in 7-Up; beat well.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 (9-inch) cake pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: low-fat shrimp scampi
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions, but do not add salt.
While pasta is cooking, in a large skillet, heat broth over medium heat.
Add Garlic and Onion; cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes.
Stir in Shrimp, Parsley, Basil, Cilantro, Lemon Juice and Red Pepper Flakes.
Cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp are just opaque, about 5 minutes.
Drain pasta in a colander.
Arrange pasta on serving plates.
Spoon shrimp mixture over pasta.
Serve immediately.

title: cock and bull stew
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onion in small amount of oil until tender. Set aside.
Brown beef in oil and return onion to pan.
Add water, steak sauce, bouillon, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add chicken and cook for 30 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 45 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni toss
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Cook peas; drain.
Mix macaroni, peas, cheese, gherkins, mayo and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peruvian sauce
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until thick, stirring often.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Good on hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: buttermilk
directions: Mix together and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: milnot cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together, then mix jello and cream cheese mixture together, adding vanilla and lemon juice.
Whip Milnot, then fold into other mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch graham cracker crust in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until stiff and serve.

title: cranberry salad 1
directions: Mix jello in boiling water until dissolved.
Add all ingredients, mixing well, and pour into mold.
Refrigerate.
This may be made several days ahead of time and will keep in refrigerator for about 2 weeks.

title: better than anything pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Divide between two crusts and chill before serving.
Pie may be frozen for later enjoyment.

title: german potato salad
directions: This is best to make the day before so all the flavors marinate together.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time. Then add remaining ingredients.
Knead dough on floured board. Cut with biscuit cutters.
Bake at 325° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, sugar, and salt.
Then combine soft butter, eggs, vanilla, milk, mashed bananas, and chopped nuts.
Add to dry ingredients. Pour into two greased and lightly floured 8 x 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: neapolitan cream cheese cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, cream cheese, milk and oil. Separate mixture into 3 separate bowls.
In bowl, add vanilla.
In second bowl, add Strawberry Quik.
In third bowl, add Nestle chocolate.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour pink mixture in first, then vanilla and white and last would be chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Use 1 cup of confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon of rum or water to make glaze when cake is done.

title: pound cheese cake
directions: Add butter, cream cheese, flour, oil, milk, sugar, eggs one at a time and cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
